OUT! STUMPED! Easy as you like! First Test wicket for Dewald Brevis and it's all over for Zimbabwe! Brevis spots Tanaka charging down the track and pushes it down the leg side, on the shorter side. Chivanga fails to get any bat on it as he looks to help it away. The keeper, Kyle Verreynne moves to his left swiftly and gathers it cleanly. Tanaka turns around and tries to plonk his bat inside the crease but Kyle is quick enough in taking the bails off.
Tanaka Chivanga st K Verreynne b D Brevis 1 (22b 0x4 0x6)
Spinning away, short and outside off, Tanaka Chivanga covers the off stump and makes the leave.
Full and turning away, on off, solidly defended by Blessing.
FOUR! Up and over! Keshav Maharaj offers flight again, full and outside off, Blessing winds up and swings through to loft it over mid off. Corbin Bosch gives it a chase and slides but in vain.
Even slower this time, on off, Blessing Muzarabani defends it off the front foot.
Slows it down, full and on middle and leg, Blessing swings again but fails to connect this time and wears it on the front pad.
SIX! Tonked! A bit too full, on middle, Blessing Muzarabani has a hoick across the line and nails the hit over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Tossed up, full and on off, Blessing Muzarabani goes inside out over cover. Corbin Bosch from mid off, turns around and goes after it. Saves the boundary and the batters run two.
Beaten! Full and in the channel on off, this zips through, Tanaka Chivanga pokes and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Kwena Maphaka goes short again but this is well outside off, Tanaka Chivanga follows the ball as he looks to ramp it over the slip cordon but misses.

Ouch, nasty! Kwena Maphaka bangs in a well-directed bumper at the left shoulder. Tanaka Chivanga takes his eyes off the ball and looks to fend it down. Wears it on the glove but it drops down and away from the man at short leg.
On middle and leg, on a short of a length, Tanaka defends it with a straight bat.
Full and attacking the stumps, pushed back to the bowler.
Angling in from around the wicket and it straightens off the deck, on a back of a length, outside off, Tanaka Chivanga tucks his bat inside the line and lets it go.
Turning away, outside off, on a length, left alone by Blessing.
Slower through the air and more air on this one, around off, Blessing Muzarabani looks to go over cover. Gets it off the outer half to backward point.
SIX! All the way! Right in the wheelhouse, on off, tossed up, Blessing Muzarabani gets low to get under the ball and clubs it over mid-wicket for a six.
FOUR! Thumped! Dewald Brevis drags the length back, around off, Blessing hangs back and stays leg side of the ball. Flat bats it past the non-striker for four more.
FOUR! Agricultural! Floated up, low full toss, on off, Blessing Muzarabani clears his front leg and swipes it through backward square leg for a boundary.
Flat and short, on off, Blessing Muzarabani hangs back to stab it down.
Nails the yorker, on off. Tanaka Chivanga digs it to the off side.
Digs it short, on off. Tanaka Chivanga looks to ramp it, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, on the stumps. Tanaka Chivanga defends it to cover.

A huge appeal of LBW but the umpire stays unmoved! Bowls it on a good length, angling onto the pads. Tanaka Chivanga looks to defend but gets beaten and wears it on the pad. Looks like it's going down the leg side.
Goes fuller and off. Tanaka Chivanga gets on the front foot and works it to cover.
Yorker on the leg stump. Tanaka Chivanga blocks it back.
Tossed up, on off. Tanaka Chivanga looks to slog across the line. Gets an outside edge that lands beyond point for a single.
A drag down, around leg. Tanaka Chivanga goes for the wild slog but misses.
Too full, on middle and leg. Tanaka Chivanga pushes this to mid on for no run.
Fuller on off, Tanaka Chivanga leaves it alone.
A tailing yorker on the leg stump. Tanaka Chivanga gets down his bat in time and pushes it back.
Fuller on off, Tanaka Chivanga blocks it out.
On a good length, on middle and leg. Blessing Muzarabani looks to block, but gets beaten and wears it on the front pad.
Nails the yorker, just on the fourth stump line. Blessing Muzarabani swings and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Short and outside off. Blessing Muzarabani lets it go.
A bit too wide outside off, yorker. Blessing Muzarabani looks to reach out for it, but again fails to connect with it.
Bowls it on short length, wide outside off. Blessing Muzarabani goes for a big swing but misses it.
Bowls it very full, outside off. Blessing Muzarabani looks to dig it out on the off side but fails to get any bat onto it.
Quicker and fuller on off, Tanaka Chivanga blocks this out as well.
Fuller on off, Tanaka Chivanga defends it out.

OUT! CAUGHT AT FIRST SLIP! Keshav Maharaj dangles the carrot just outside off, it hits a footmark and shoots up a bit. Wellington Masakadza gets lured into the drive and ends up edging this off the outside edge to first slip. Wiaan Mulder moves a shade to his right and holds onto this.
Wellington Masakadza c W Mulder b K Maharaj 57 (92b 9x4 0x6)
Full and on off, defended off the front foot by Wellington.
Slower around off, spinning back into the batter. Wellington Masakadza rocks back to flick it away but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Way too full, outside off. Wellington Masakadza goes for the drive but is late on the shot and misses.
Short, on the off stump. Blessing Muzarabani rocks back and defends this one.
Full and outside off. Blessing Muzarabani once again goes for a wild swing but misses it to the keeper.

EDGED AND FOUR! Bowls it on the good length, angling into the middle and leg. Blessing Muzarabani stays leg side and looks to go over long on but gets an inside edge to the left of the keeper to fine leg for a boundary.
Swing and a miss! Drags the length back, on off. Blessing Muzarabani goes for a wild slog but misses it and gets beaten on the inside edge.
Fuller and outside off. Blessing Muzarabani drives it to backward point.
Fuller, angling onto the pads. Blessing Muzarabani flicks it to mid on and the fielder there dives to his right to stop it.
Pushed through on off, Wellington Masakadza rocks back and defends this one.
Tossed up full and on off, Wellington Masakadza goes for the cover drive but gets it edged to backward point for no run.
Tossed up on leg, Wellington Masakadza drills this to mid on for no run.
Flatter around middle and off, Blessing Muzarabani tucks this through mid-wicket for one.
Floated around off, Blessing Muzarabani pokes at it but gets beaten.
Swing and a miss. Fuller on off, turning away from the batter. Blessing Muzarabani swings at it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On the full length, outside off. Wellington Masakadza throws his hands at it and drives it to the left of cover. The fielder there gives it a chase and keeps it to two.
Short length, angling into the batter. Wellington Masakadza hops back and blocks it.
On a good length, on off. Wellington Masakadza works it to the gully region.
Goes fuller, on off. Blessing Muzarabani looks to drive but gets an outside edge to backward point for one.
On a length, outside off. Blessing Muzarabani lets it be.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! FIVE WICKETS FOR BOSCH! Corbin Bosch gets his maiden Test match fifer and he is elated! Bowls it on the back of a length, coming into the batter from outside off. Vincent Masekesa gets on his toes and looks to punch it away to the off side but gets a thick inside edge that rattles the off stump. Vincent Masekesa departs on 3 (10), and South Africa are just two wickets away from the win.
Vincent Masekesa b C Bosch 3 (10b 0x4 0x6)
Too full, around off, Wellington Masakadza fails to get underneath and thumps this to silly mid off for no run.

FOUR! Driven handsomely past the fielder at short cover for a boundary from Wellington Masakadza. This was tossed up and around off, Wellington Masakadza strides out in front and drives this well and all along the ground for a boundary.
Tossed up around off, Wellington Masakadza smashes this powerfully back to the bowler. Keshav Maharaj manages to get both hands behind this but the ball pops out. Would've been a crowd catch.
Fuller around off, Vincent Masekesa drives this through extra cover for one.
Swing and a miss. A proper number 9 on strike in Vincent Masekesa. Flighted over the eyeline of the batter and he swings at it. The ball spins away and beats him.
Fuller around off, Wellington Masakadza drives this through cover for one.
Goes fuller, angling onto the pads. Vincent Masekesa flicks it to the mid-wicket region for a couple of runs.
On a back of a length, on off, Vincent stays leg side and dabs it to backward point.
Short and outside off. Vincent Masekesa gets on top of the bounce and steers it to backward point.
Slanting in, on a nagging length, on off, Vincent Masekesa covers the line and blocks.
On a length, angling onto the stumps. Vincent Masekesa looks to clip it but misses it and wears on the pads. A huge appeal of LBW, but the umpire stays unmoved.
Bowls it on short length, outside off. Vincent Masekesa leaves it alone.
Excellent by Keshav Maharaj as he beats the batter on the outside edge. Quicker and flatter around off, Wellington Masakadza prods in front to defend this but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tossed up on off, Wellington Masakadza defends this out as well.
Floated on off, Wellington Masakadza pushes this back to the bowler's left.
Full and on off, Wellington Masakadza lunges to defend. Gets beaten to the turn on the inside but the ball appears to be going down the leg.
Solidly defended off the front foot.
Fuller around off, Wellington Masakadza defends this one.
Bowls it on a short length, outside off from over the wicket. Vincent Masekesa leaves it alone.

OUT! CAUGHT! It's a stunning catch from Tony de Zorzi, and Craig Ervine falls one run short of his half century! Corbin Bosch bowls it on a good length, angling onto the pads. Craig Ervine sets up to flick it away but the ball hits the upper half of the bat and it goes to the left of Tony de Zorzi at short leg. Tony sticks out his left hand to take an absolute blinder. Craig Ervine departs on 49 (77).
Craig Ervine (c) c Td Zorzi b C Bosch 49 (77b 7x4 0x6)
On a nagging length, angling across. Craig Ervine lunges forward to defend but gets an outside edge to gully, and the fielder there dives to his right to stop it.
Short length, on the sticks. Craig Ervine ducks underneath it.
On a good length, outside off. Craig Ervine hops back and punches it past cover for a couple of runs.
On a length, on the stumps. Stays a bit low and Craig Ervine gets behind the line and blocks it.
Fuller on the pads, WM tucks this to short leg.
Tossed up wide of off, Wellington Masakadza lets it sail back to the keeper.
Fuller around off, Wellington Masakadza defends this.
Pushed through on off, Wellington Masakadza defends this out.
Goes the other way around now. Full and on off, a single to deep point off a reverse sweep.
FOUR! Swept well for a boundary. Tossed up on the pads, Craig Ervine sweeps this uppish and wide of deep mid-wicket to his left for four.

FOUR! MAIDEN TEST FIFTY for Wellington Masakadza! Corbin Bosch bowls it on a good length, angling away from the batter. Wellington Masakadza steers it along the ground to the right of backward point for a boundary to bring up his half-century.
Short length, on the stumps. Wellington Masakadza ducks underneath it.
On a length, on middle. Craig Ervine tucks it to square leg for one.
In the air and safe! Bowls it on full and on the pads. Wellington Masakadza clips it uppishly but in the vacant deep square leg region for one.
On a length, on pads. Wellington Masakadza defends it right under his eyes.
On a hard length, on off, Wellington Masakadza steers it wide of backward point for a couple of runs.
Full and on off, another confident block off the front foot.
Fuller on off, Craig Ervine defends it.
Tossed up, wide of off, Craig Ervine jams this down.
Fuller around off, Craig Ervine looks to block it but gets beaten.

Tossed up on the pads, Craig Ervine lunges to block but the ball kicks up a bit and turns sharply to catch the inside edge. Luckily for Ervine, it falls in the vacant backward short leg region and evades Tony de Zorzi to his left.
Bowls it on a length, on off from over the wicket. Craig Ervine works it to the backward point region for couple of runs.
Flighted around off, Wellington Masakadza defends it out. That will be LUNCH on Day 4!
Short of a length around off, Wellington Masakadza thumps this back to the bowler for no run.
Too full on off, Wellington Masakadza defends it.
Googly around off, Craig Ervine guides this to deep third for a single.
Haltracker around leg, Wellington Masakadza swipes it straight onto the shoes of Tony de Zorzi at short leg. The ball deflects to deep square for one.
Full and on off, Craig Ervine blocks away through cover for one.
Pushed through on off, Wellington Masakadza defends this.
Full toss around off, Wellington Masakadza gets lured into a wild heave and ends up lofting this towards long off for a couple.
Tossed up on off, Wellington Masakadza blocks this out.
Floated flat around off, Wellington Masakadza looks to block out off the back foot but gets beaten.
Tossed up on off, WM blocks it.
Full and on off, Wellington Masakadza pushes this to cover.
Straight one, on off, Craig Ervine edges this onto the pads for no run.
Flighted wide of off, Craig Ervine defends this too.
Fuller and flatter around off, Craig Ervine defends this out as well.
Quicker and fuller on off, Craig Ervine edges this off the inside to short leg.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Craig Ervine hops up on his toes and punches this past point for four.
Fuller on middle and off. Craig Ervine defends.
Pushed through on off, Wellington Masakadza blocks this out.
Length dragged back a bit, Wellington Masakadza prods in front and blocks.
Slider from round the wicket, Wellington Masakadza does well to defend it.
Slower through the air, on off, defended.
Tossed up around off, Craig Ervine reverse sweeps it to deep point for one.
Pushed through on off, Craig defends it.
Back of a length, going across the batter. Wellington Masakadza leaves it all alone.
On a length, angling into the batter, Craig Ervine flicks this to deep square for one.
A well-directed short-pitched delivery around the rib cage of Wellington Masakadza. The batter gets into an awkward position and manages to get it away through square leg for one.
Good length on leg, Wellington Masakadza defends this.
Short-pitched, on off, Wellington Masakadza blocks this out to cover-point.
On a length, angling away from the batter. Wellington Masakadza looked to bail out of the block initially but ends up blocking it off the bottom of his bat.
Pushed through on off, Craig Ervine gets right on top of it and jams this out.
Blocked off the front foot this time.
Fuller on off, Craig Ervine defends this out.
A bit closer to off, Craig Ervine steps across and looks for the ramp but doesn't connect well.
Touch fuller, on off, Craig Ervine gets on top of it and blocks this as well.
Tossed up on off, Craig Ervine blocks it out.

Back of a length, angling in sharply onto the batter. Wellington Masakadza looks to get it away somehow and ends up getting beaten all ends up. Luckily for Wellington Masakadza, the ball bounced over the stumps.
Short and wide outside off, Wellington Masakadza leaves it.
Full and on the pads, Craig Ervine glances this to deep square for a single.
Back of a length on the pads, Wellington Masakadza turns it down to fine leg for a single.
Short-pitched around off, Wellington Masakadza swings at it but misses out.
Good length on the pads, Craig Ervine milks this on the leg side for one.
On off, defended off the back foot this time.
Quicker and fuller on middle and leg, Wellington Masakadza blocks it out.
Pushed through on off, Craig gets it edged off the outside through short third for one.
FOUR! Fuller, wide outside off, Craig Ervine picks it up and goes for the reverse sweep. Connects well and the ball races to the third man fence for four runs.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Craig Ervine tucks this to mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, Craig Ervine looks to defend this off his front foot but misses and wears it on his pads. Loud appeal for LBW but the umpire turns it down.
Yorker on off, Wellington Masakadza blocks it out.
FOUR! Hits it behind square on off for four more. Back of a length on off, Wellington Masakadza opens the face of his bat and cuts this behind square for four.
Good length on middle and leg, Wellington Masakadza defends this out.

FOUR! Wellington Masakadza is enjoying his time in the middle with the bat in his hand. Pitched up on off, Wellington Masakadza strides to the pitch of it and drives this all along the carpet, through point for four.

Back of a length around off, Craig Ervine hops up on his toes and punches this past cover for one. A bit of mix-up between the batters but throw at the wrong end, non-striker's end, saves Wellington Masakadza, who was halfway down the track.
Brilliantly bowled, in the corridor of uncertainty around off, Craig Ervine presses forward to punch this but gets beaten.
Fuller in length, outside off, Masakadza drives a bit away from his body towards mid off.
Nipping back in, on a back of a length, on top of off, Wellington Masakadza hops and keeps it out.
FOUR! Easily done! Wiaan Mulder errs in both line and length. Serves it short and wide on off, there to be put away. Masakadza frees his arms and cuts it through cover-point for a boundary.
On middle and leg, on a nagging length, knocked to mid on.
Just outside the off stump, on a length. Wellington Masakadza is unable to free his arms in the way he would have liked. Mistimes the shot to mid off.
Slanting in, on the off stump, on a good length, Masakadza covers the line and plays it back to the bowler.
On a hard length, on top of off, Craig Ervine gets on top of the bounce to stab it down the deck.
Around off, on a good length, Craig Ervine shoulders arms.
Tighter line, around the off stump, on a nagging length, Masakadza taps it wide of cover for one.
FOUR! Thumped! Wide on off, on a length, Masakadza frees his arms and crunches it through covers for a boundary.
On a hard length, on middle, Wellington Masakadza hurriedly tucks it to square leg.
Kwena Maphaka comes into the attack and angles it in from over the wicket, on a good length, on off, left alone by Masakadza.
Drags the length back and the line is around the off stump, Masakadza pushes it wide of point and takes a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Mulder sprays it on the pads, on a length, Masakadza brings his wrists into play and whips it up and over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Leading edge but safe! Fuller in length, on middle, Masakadza looks to work it away with the angle on the leg side. Closes the bat face early and gets a leading edge that drops in front of point.
On middle and leg, on a length, Wellington Masakadza gets his bat out in front to defend.
This straightens off the deck, on a good length, on off from around the wicket, WM defends inside the line and gets beaten.
Just around the off stump, on a hard length, Masakadza rides the bounce and keeps it out on the off side.
Delivers it on a short of a length, on off, jabbed to mid-wicket by Ervine.
A half-volley, wide on off, Wellington Masakadza frees his arms and drives it to the left of point. Matthew Breetzke goes after it and prevents the boundary. Masakadza collects three runs.
Short and wide on off, Masakadza goes for the cut but ends up chopping it down on the off side.
Pitched up, on off, Ervine does not go through the shot completely and just eases it to the right of cover. The fielder gives it a chase and cuts it off. Three runs taken.
This kicks up a bit, on a hard length, on middle, Masakadza fends it down off the gloves behind square on the leg side for one.
On a back of a length, on middle, Ervine hops and nudges it to the right of deep fine leg for a single.
Sprayed on the pads, on a length, Masakadza flicks it to the left of mid-wicket and collects a couple of runs.
Angled in, on a back of a length, on off, Wellington Masakadza pats it to mid on.
Bowled from wide of the crease on the around-the-wicket angle, outside off, on a good length, Wellington lets it be.
On off, Wellington Masakadza pushes it to mid off.
On a hard length, on off, Wellington Masakadza presents an angled bat and stabs it down.

CHANCE? Did it go off the bat? Wiaan Mulder's reaction suggests so. Angling in and then nibbling away, on a good length, Wellington is squared up in defence. The ball nips away to brush the outside edge and it goes low to the left of the keeper. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left but fails to cling on.
On a length, angling across the batter. Craig Ervine lets it be.
Full and off. Craig Ervine gets on the front foot and blocks it to cover.
FOUR! Nicely clipped! Codi Yusuf overpitches it on the middle and off. Craig Ervine flicks it nicely along the ground to the left of the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
On a good length, on off. Craig Ervine prods forward and defends it to the off side.
On a hard length, on middle, Ervine tucks it to mid-wicket.
Angling away, on a hard length, Ervine steers it off the back foot to backward point.

Slows it down and gets the ball to drop on the batter, Wellington Masakadza reaches out in front to smother the spin but fails to do so. Gets hit on the front pad but outside the line of the off stump.
Pushed through, on off, Wellington Masakadza lunges to block it out.

FOUR! Keshav Maharaj gives a bit more air and bowls it fuller, on off. Wellington Masakadza comes forward and gets to the pitch of the ball to drive it along the ground through the cover region for a boundary.
Full and on off, Wellington Masakadza defends it well.
Fuller and slower, on off. Wellington Masakadza leans forward and drives it through the cover region. Kwena Maphaka gives it a chase and keeps it to a couple of runs.
Floated up, on off, Ervine knocks it down to long on for a single.
On the off stump, on a good length, Wellington Masakadza pats it back to the bowler with a straight bat.

EDGED AND FOUR! Bowls it on a fuller length, on off. Wellington Masakadza looks to defend it but gets an outside edge to the slip cordon. The ball does not carry to first slip and goes between his legs to race away for a boundary.
Hits the length hard, on the middle and leg. Wellington Masakadza looks to clip it on the leg side but gets beaten and wears it high on the pad. An appeal of LBW but the umpire stays unmoved.
On the back of a length, angling across the batter. Wellington Masakadza lets it go.

OUT! CAUGHT! Codi Yusuf is on a roll! Three wickets in as many overs for Yusuf today. A nothing shot from Tafadzwa Tsiga and he pays the ultimate price. Delivers it on a back of a length, well outside off, Tsiga hangs on the back foot and has a fiddle at the delivery well away from his body. Gets an outside edge that travels quickly to fourth slip and Corbin Bosch takes a sharp catch to his right.
Tafadzwa Tsiga (wk) c C Bosch b C Yusuf 0 (4b 0x4 0x6)
On off, on a good length, Craig Ervine jabs a bit with hard hands. Gets an outside edge that goes down on the ground. The gully fielder makes a half-stop with a dive to his right. A single is taken.
Loopy delivery, on off, Craig Ervine takes it on the full and sweeps it on the bounce to the man at deep square leg. They cross.
Switches to over the wicket and pushes it through, on off, Craig Ervine goes deep in the crease to block.

FOUR! This time from reverse sweep! Bowls it loopy and slower, on middle. Craig Ervine gets down on one knee and gets in the position for the reverse sweep and plays it along the ground to the right of the backward point region for a boundary.
Looped up, just outside the off stump, Craig keeps it out off the front foot.
FOUR! Keshav Maharaj serves it slower and fuller, on off. Craig Ervine puts the dancing shoes on and gets to the pitch of the ball to loft it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up, on middle, Craig Ervine lunges to defend.
On short length, outside off. Tafadzwa Tsiga leaves it alone.
Another beauty from Codi Yusuf! Bowls it on a good length, on off. The ball nips back sharply and goes over the off stump. Tafadzwa Tsiga shoulders arms at it.
On the nagging length, angling into the batter from middle. Tafadzwa Tsiga looks to clip but misses it and wears it on the thigh pad.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Another one bites the dust. Wickets off successive overs for the debutant! Nice channel from Codi, just outside the off stump, on a good length. Wessly follows the line of the ball away from his body. Presents a straight bat to block but the ball angles in and then straightens to graze the outside edge. The keeper, Kyle Verreynne, does the rest behind the wicket.
Wessly Madhevere c K Verreynne b C Yusuf 0 (8b 0x4 0x6)
On the back of a length, on off. Wessly Madhevere shoulders arms at it.
On the hard length, angling into the batter. Wessly Madhevere gets beaten on the inside edge with a bit of extra bounce and wears it on the thigh pad.
Fuller and on middle. Craig Ervine clips it to backward square leg.
FOUR! Good shot! Tossed up, on off, on a length, Craig Ervine reaches out in front and rolls his wrists over the ball to sweep it all along the ground through backward square leg for a boundary.
Fuller and off. Craig Ervine prods forward and drives it to cover.
Very full, on off, squeezed out to mid off by Craig.
Sharp turn! Tossed up and outside off. Craig Ervine gets on the front foot to defend, but the ball turns sharply and goes past his leg stump.
Full and on off, whipped to mid-wicket by Ervine.
Back of a length, on off. Wessly Madhevere plays it with the soft hands and gets an outside edge which falls short to the man at gully.
BEATEN! Hits the length hard, and it just nips away from the fourth stump line. Wessly Madhevere looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
A bit too wide on off, on a nagging length, another easy leave for Wessly.
Full ball, sprayed down leg. A diving take by Kyle Verreynne to his left.
On a good length, outside off, Wessly Madhevere lets it be.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Codi Yusuf strikes on the first ball of his spell on Day 4! Bowls it on a good length and angling across the batter. Prince Masvaure is better off leaving the ball alone but lunges forward to defend. The ball kicks up a bit and catches the outside edge. Wiaan Mulder at second slip stays low to take a good catch. Prince Masvaure departs on 12 (76).
Prince Masvaure c W Mulder b C Yusuf 12 (76b 1x4 0x6)
Fuller and on off. Craig Ervine prods forward and blocks it off the inner half of the bat back to the bowler.
On off, on a length, blocked out by Ervine off the front foot.
Nicely tossed up and fuller, turning into the batter from over the wicket. Craig Ervine looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses it on the inside edge onto the pads.
Looped up, full and on middle, Masvaure drives it in front of the man at a deepish mid on for one.
Slower and fuller, on off from around the wicket. Prince Masvaure lunges forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up, full and on off, Craig Ervine wrists it to deep mid-wicket and crosses over.
Bowls it on a hard length, angling into the batter from around the wicket. Prince Masvaure hops back and blocks it to the off side.
On a length, on middle and leg. Craig Ervine tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
On the short length, on the off stump. This stays a bit low, and Craig Ervine works it off the toe end of the bat to the mid on region.
On a good length, on middle and off. Craig Ervine gets behind the line and taps it back to the bowler.
Bends his back and digs it short, outside leg. Craig Ervine ducks underneath it. WIDED for height.
Hits the length hard, on off. Craig Ervine rides the bounce and blocks it back to the bowler.
Bowls it on the back of a length, angling across the batter. Craig Ervine guides it to gully.
A maiden by Keshav Maharaj! Flatter and shorter, on middle, Prince stays back to keep it out.
Turning into the pads, on a length, Prince Masvaure defends inside the line and gets beaten. Gets hit on the front pad.
Slower through the air, fuller as well, on middle, Prince clips it to mid-wicket.
Beaten! Sliding across the left-hander, not all that short, Masvaure goes back and looks to push it away on the off side but misses.
Attacking the front pad, on a length, Masvaure blocks it with his bat close to the front pad.
Maharaj comes from around the wicket to the left-hander. Tosses it up, full and on off, Prince Masvaure defends well.
Corbin Bosch goes fuller this time and pushes it across, Craig Ervine is drawn forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Banged in short, over middle, Craig Ervine ducks under it.
Delivers it on a hard length, on off, Ervine pats it down on the off side.
On off, on a back of a length, Craig stabs it down on the off side.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! End of Sean Williams' struggles against Corbin Bosch! A massive blow to Zimbabwe as the centurion from the first innings falls. On middle and leg, on a nagging length, Sean Williams stays rooted to the crease and tries to bring his wrists into play. Shapes up to turn it away on the leg side with a closed bat face. Closes the bat face early and gets a leading edge that goes straight up behind the wicket. The keeper, Kyle Verreynne, calls for it and takes a couple of steps backwards to take a safe catch.
Sean Williams c K Verreynne b C Bosch 26 (18b 5x4 0x6)

Beaten! Corbin continues to get the ball to go across the left-hander from over the wicket, on a good length, just around the off stump, Sean Williams follows the ball before deciding to withdraw the bat.
More air on this one and wide as well, Masvaure looks to drive this full ball through the off side but miscues it back to the bowler.
Floats it up, full and on off, Masvaure defends it off the front foot.
Fuller and slower, on off, Williams lunges and flicks it to the left of mid on for a single.
This turns back in sharply, on a nagging length, around leg, played with the turn to mid-wicket.
Flatter and shorter, on off, Sean Williams pats it down the deck.

FOUR! Fine shot! 5th boundary in 13 balls for Sean. Tossed up by Keshav, on off, Williams reaches out in front and takes it on the full. Plays the reverse sweep all along the ground to the right of backward point for a boundary.
Slanting across, over the top of the off stump, Masvaure makes a watchful leave.
Dug in short by Corbin, over middle and leg, Prince ducks under it.
On a nagging length, on middle, tucked down to the right of short leg by Prince Masvaure.

Pitched up by Corbin, on off. Again, no foot movement from Sean Williams, knocks it down the ground to the left of mid off. Kwena Maphaka goes after it and slides to prevent the ball from reaching the fence. Three runs taken.
On a back of a length, on middle, Sean hops and dabs it down on the off side.
Deviating away off the seam from a good length, Sean Williams has a slight poke at the delivery before opting to withdraw his bat. The ball whistles past the outside edge.
Darted in, on a length, on off, kept out off the front foot.
Turning in, on a length, on off, Prince Masvaure blocks it out.
FOUR! Nicely done! Very full, on middle, Prince Masvaure gets down and sweeps it fine to the left of short fine leg. Corbin Bosch gives it a chase but in vain.
Outside off, Prince Masvaure defends this full ball solidly.
Slows it down and hangs it up, full and wide on off, Prince Masvaure presses forward for the drive. Miscues it off the inner half to mid on.
Floated up, on off, driven back to Maharaj by Prince.
Beaten all ends up! On a hard length, on off, Sean Williams does not get behind the line of the ball. Hangs on the back foot to cover the line of the ball and is beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! Edgy! This squares Sean up, on a good length, on middle, Williams opts to stay leg side of the ball and tries to turn it away on the leg side. The ball nips away to catch the leading edge and it goes to the left of gully for a boundary.
FOUR! Hit with disdain! Corbin Bosch goes into the wicket but fails to get it high enough and the line is around off. Sean Williams stands tall and drags the pull in front of square for a boundary.
Banged in on a shortish length, on off, Prince Masvaure rides the bounce and drops it beside the pitch on the off side for one.
On a back of a length, on top of off, Williams pats it off the back foot wide of cover for a single.
Play and a miss! On a length, angled across, Sean Williams is rooted to the crease and fiddles at the delivery away from his body. Gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full and around off, Prince Masvaure plays it back to the bowler.

Nearly dragged it back onto the stumps! Keshav Maharaj slows it down and drags the length back slightly, outside off, Prince lunges to smother the spin but the ball drops on him and spins to catch the inside edge and rolls to leg slip.
Beaten! This does not turn and keeps straight, full and outside off, Prince Masvaure is drawn forward in the defence. The ball sneaks past the outside edge.
Loopy delivery, this drops on the batter, around off, Prince Masvaure jams it out.
Pushed through, short and outside off, Sean goes back and pushes it wide of cover for a single.
Keshav tries to toss it up but ends up serving a low full toss, on off, Prince Masvaure mistimes the drive to the right of mid off where Codi Yusuf cuts it off with a dive. They cross.

FOUR! Edged away! Another one from Corbin Bosch that is pushed across the left-hander from over the wicket, on a nagging length, Sean Williams does not move his feet at all and just goes at it with his hands. Gets an outside edge that goes between third slip and gully. The gully fielder flies to his right but the ball evades him and goes behind for a boundary.
FOUR! Sean Williams is up and running! Angled across, on a length, Sean lets his hands flow into the shot and caresses it through covers for a boundary.
Going across, on a length, Sean Williams defends a bit away from the body but manages to negotiate the hat-trick ball safely.

OUT! TAKEN! WOW! What a start for South Africa! Corbin Bosch strikes on the very first ball of the day. Nick Welch goes for a golden duck. Bosch steams in from over the wicket, bends his back and digs in a well-directed bumper. Gets it high enough to trouble the batter, around the left shoulder. Nick rises to get on top of the bounce but the ball keeps climbing onto him. Welch tries to take the bottom hand of the bat but the ball catches the gloves and lobs tamely for Tony de Zorzi to take a dolly at short leg. Corbin Bosch is on a hat-trick.
Nick Welch c Td Zorzi b C Bosch 0 (1b 0x4 0x6)

OUT! CAUGHT! Oh, no, no no! Zimbabwe will be distressed! Lhuan-dre Pretorius takes the catch at third slip from an extended over in the day. On a length, outside off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano looks to push it but gets a thick edge. The ball carries towards third slip, where Lhuan-dre Pretorius takes a good low catch. Corbin Bosch provides a breakthrough, and it will be STUMPS on Day 3!
Takudzwanashe Kaitano c L Pretorius b C Bosch 12 (62b 0x4 0x6)
Short, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano stands tall and fends it back to the bowler.
Short, outside off, with some turn. Prince Masvaure leaves it alone.
Short, turning in, Prince Masvaure looks to block it but wears it on his thigh pad.
Flatter, on leg, Prince Masvaure flicks it to the fielder at short third.
Similar delivery, on off, Prince Masvaure lunges and blocks it back for the third time.
Too full, on off, Prince Masvaure leans on and blocks again.
Flighted up, on off, Prince Masvaure leans on and blocks it.
Too full, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano pushes it to the fielder at mid off.
Length again, on leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano flicks it to the fielder at short leg. Tony de Zorzi does well to stay low and make the stop to his left.
On a length, on leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano flicks it to the fielder at short leg.
Short and down leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leaves it alone.
Short and wide, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano tucks it to the fielder at short leg. He does well to stop it. Dot.
Slower through the air, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano flicks it to mid on for one.
Flighted up, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano eases it back to the bowler.
Another one on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano blocks it solidly again.
Floated up, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano blocks it back.
Full, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leans on and blocks it.

Slower through the air, outside off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano drives it uppishly past the cover fielder, who makes a dive but the ball evades him. The ball goes towards deep cover as the batters collect two runs.
A sharp bouncer, on off, Prince Masvaure ducks under it.
Short and wide, Prince Masvaure leaves it alone.
Length, outside off, Prince Masvaure leaves it alone.
Short, on off, Prince Masvaure ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano hangs back and punches it to cover for one.
On a length, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano stands tall and blocks it back.
Keeps it full again, Prince Masvaure leans on and blocks it back.

DROPPED! Full, turning in, Prince Masvaure looks to block it but miscues it to the fielder at short leg. He makes a dive to take the catch, but the ball lands just short. The replay later shows that the ball did carry and hit Tony de Zorzi on his right thumb, but he failed to take the catch. So this will indeed go down as a dropped catch. A difficult one, though.
Short, on middle, Prince Masvaure hangs back and blocks it back.
Too full, on off, Prince Masvaure pushes it to cover.
Lands it outside off, Prince Masvaure looks to block it but misses as the ball spins back in sharply to beat the bat on the inside edge. The leg slip fielder does well to stop it.
Fuller, outside off, Prince Masvaure blocks it back.
Length, outside off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leaves it alone.

NO BALL! My word! That was nasty from Kwena Maphaka! A high full toss, down leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano somehow manages to duck under it as the ball races away to the fine leg fence. The umpire signals a no ball for height!
Short and wide, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leaves it alone.
Too full, down leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano looks to flick it but misses.
Down the leg side, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leaves.
Short, outside off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leaves it alone.
On a length, on leg, Prince Masvaure helps it fine for one.
Flatter, on middle and leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano looks to flick it but miscues it to the point fielder.
Short, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano knocks it down the ground to the left of mid on for a brace.
Sways it on leg, Takudzwanashe Kaitano flicks it to the fielder at backward square leg.
Fuller, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano pushes it to the point fielder.
Turn and bounce, outside off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano looks to block it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Too full, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano pushes it to mid off.
On a length, on leg, Prince Masvaure fends it back towards the bowler.
Short, outside off, Prince Masvaure has a fiddle but cannot adjust with the bounce.
Too full, angling down leg, Prince Masvaure looks to flick it but wears it on his pads. A loud appeal, but the finger stays down. Perhaps, missing leg.
FIVE WIDES! Bonus runs! Wayward, down the leg side, Prince Masvaure leaves. The keeper has no chance to stop it as the ball races away.
Similar delivery, outside off, Prince Masvaure looks to slap it but gets a bottom edge as the ball bounces back towards the keeper.
Short and wide, Prince Masvaure shoulders arms.
Back of a length, on off, Prince Masvaure blocks it back.
Short, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano punches it through covers for one.
Turn and bounce, on off, Prince Masvaure looks to block it but edges it to short third for one.
Short, on off, Prince Masvaure stands tall and blocks it to the left of the bowler.
Lands it on middle, Prince Masvaure blocks it to the short leg fielder.
Full again, slower through the air, Prince Masvaure flicks it to square leg.
Floated up, on off, Prince Masvaure flicks it to the fielder at short leg.
Down leg, on a good length, Kaitano lets it be.
Play and a miss! Full and pushed across the batter, Takudzwanashe Kaitano presses forward and has a feel for the delivery. Gets beaten on the outside edge.
A loud shout for LBW but turned down! Seemed to have pitched outside leg. Shaping back in, on a nagging length, on leg, Kaitano is late on the flick and wears it above the knee roll on the front pad.

On a hard length, around leg, Kaitano hops and tucks it past short leg to his right. There is a bit of hesitation about the second run but they do cross over eventually. The throw comes in from the deep towards the batting end and Kyle Verreynne is up to the stumps to whip the bails off. The third umpire is called in and the replays show that Kaitano has made it comfortably.
Angled across the right-hander, on a length, left alone by Kaitano.
With a deepish short leg in place, Kwena Maphaka steams in from over the wicket and goes into the wicket. The line is down leg and Takudzwanashe Kaitano hops to tickle it fine but misses.
Just outside the off stump, on a good length, Prince covers the off stump and shoulders arms.
This nips back in sharply and shoots a bit as well, on off, on a hard length, Prince Masvaure hangs back and keeps it out.
Goes wide on the crease and serves it on a length, outside off, Prince lets it be.

FOUR LEG BYES! Sliding onto the pads from around the wicket, on a short of a length, Prince Masvaure misses out on the tickle. The ball brushes the thigh pad and beats the diving Kyle Verreynne to his right for a boundary.
On a back of a length, on middle, Prince flicks it to mid-wicket.
Fractionally wide, on a short of a length, Prince Masvaure cuts it hard but it goes straight to point on the bounce.
On off, on a nagging length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano hangs back and solidly defends.
On a back of a length, around off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano pushes it to point.
Moving away in the air, on a good length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano defends it with soft hands.
Fuller and on off, Kaitano presses forward and eases it past cover for a couple of runs.
On a length, on the pads, Takudzwanashe Kaitano closes the face of the bat early and gets the top edge. It lobs and drops in front of mid on.
A well-directed bumper, over middle, Takudzwanashe Kaitano hurriedly ducks under it.

Risky single! Seaming away, on off, on a good length, Kaitano drops it to the right of point and sets off for a single. Prince is a bit late in responding. Corbin Bosch gets to the ball quickly and fires in a throw at the batting end but misses. It would have been close had the throw hit.
In the corridor on off, on a good length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano makes a watchful leave.
Too wide to make the batter play, shaping away, Kaitano lets it be.
Goes full and outside off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leans for the drive and gets an inside edge onto the front pad.
This nips back in, on a length, on the off stump, Takudzwanashe Kaitano gets forward and defends with his bat close to the front pad.
On the fuller side, on off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano gets a bit squared up on the defence due to the away seam movement. Gets it off the outer half to point.
Delivers it on a length, on middle and leg, tucked to square leg by Prince.
Pushed across the left-hander, on a length, left alone by Prince.
Bangs it on a hard length, over off, Prince Masvaure rises with the bounce and keeps it out.
On middle and leg, on a length, Prince Masvaure nudges it watchfully to the right of deep fine leg for a couple of runs.
Nipping back in, on a good length, Prince works it to the left of mid-wicket and sets off for a single before being sent back by his partner.
Sprayed well down leg, Prince Masvaure lets it go. Kyle Verreynne flings hismelf to his right to make the stop.

Beaten! The ball threatens to angle in but eventually nips away off the deck, on a good length, on the off stump, Takudzwanashe Kaitano hangs his bat out to block but the ball zips past the outside edge.
Hurls it on a nagging length, on off, Kaitano jabs it from the crease to mid-wicket.
Straying on the pads, on a length, Prince Masvaure tickles it down to deep fine leg and gets off the mark with a single.
Pitched up, on the pads, Prince Masvaure is rooted to the crease and is tentative on the flick. Gets beaten on the inside edge to wear it on the front pad.

Leg bye! Jagging back in, on middle and leg, on a good length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano plants his front foot forward to turn it away on the leg side. The ball goes past the bat and clips the pads before rolling towards deep fine leg for a leg bye.
On off, on a back of a length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano pats it off the back foot to mid on.

This seams away and kicks up a bit, after landing around the line of the leg stump, Prince Masvaure shuffles a bit to get behind the line. Presents a straight bat but gets beaten on the outside edge and gets hit high on the left thigh.
Sliding in at the hips, Takudzwanashe Kaitano helps it down to deep fine leg and takes the single to open his account.
Angling in, on a hard length, on middle, Takudzwanashe Kaitano tries to work it on the leg side with a closed bat face. He is a bit late on the shot and wears it on the thigh pad.
Serves it on a back of a length, outside off, Takudzwanashe Kaitano watchfully lets it go.
Makes the batter play this time, on the off stump, on a length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano covers the line and defends.
Codi continues to be a bit too wide and short. Outside off, on a short of a length, moving away, Kaitano shoulders arms.
Pulls the length back slightly, on the off stump, Prince Masvaure stabs it down with a straight bat.
Pitched up, just outside the off stump, Prince pushes it down the deck.
On top of off, on a good length, Prince Masvaure gets behind the line and solidly defends.
Beaten! Closer to the off stump, on a nagging length, straightens off the deck, Prince goes feeling for the ball a bit and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Angling in and then nibbling away, on a length, Prince Masvaure does follow the ball initially before withdrawing his bat.
Begins from around the wicket, on a good length, in the channel on off, left alone by Prince.
Codi Yusuf starts with a maiden! Lands it on a back of a length, wide outside off, an easy leave for Kaitano.
Swinging away from the right-hander, outside off, on a good length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, outside off, a tempter for Kaitano but he resists and does not offer a shot.
Moving away in the air, outside off, on a good length, Kaitano shoulders arms.
Another one a bit too wide to make the batter play, on a good length, Kaitano is happy to let it go.
Shaping away, well outside off, on a good length, Takudzwanashe Kaitano makes the leave. The ball just about carries to the keeper, Kyle Verreynne.

OUT! CASTLED! Blessing Muzarabani wraps up the innings! On a length, on off, Kwena Maphaka swings to go down the ground with a straight bat. Plays down the wrong line and is rooted to the crease. The ball sneaks past the inside edge and goes through to uproot the off stump and the middle stump. South Africa are bowled out for 369 with a lead of 536!
Kwena Maphaka b B Muzarabani 8 (14b 0x4 1x6)

Short length, on the middle and pff. Kwena Maphaka looks to pull but gets a leading edge to the gully region. The fiedler there collects the ball and throws it at the stumps to the bowler's end, but the batter was inside the crease.
Angling away, on a back of a length, on off, Kwena Maphaka hops and keeps it out.

SIX! More of a top edge but they all count! Blessing Muzarabani digs it in short, around the left shoulder, Kwena Maphaka hops to hook it away. Gets a top edge that goes down to deep fine leg and clears the fence for a six.
Short length, outside off. Kwena Maphaka leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Codi Yusuf looks to drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! EDGED AND IT RACES AWAY! Bowls it on a nagging length, on off. Codi Yusuf looks to defend from the crease and he gets a thick outside edge that goes between the slip cordon and the gully. The ball races to the third man region for a boundary.
Short length, going down the leg. Codi Yusuf leaves it alone.
Fuller, and leg, Codi Yusuf plays all around it on the flick but that was sliding down leg.
Short length, outside off. Kwena Maphaka punches to cover for a single.
On the middle and off, on a length. Kwena Maphaka looks to flick but misses it and wears it on the pad. Uh oh, Tanaka Chivanga has overstepped and it's a NO BALL!
On a full length, outside off from over the wicket. Codi Yusuf works it to the third man region for one.
Goes fuller, angling onto the middle stump. Kwena Maphaka looks to defend it off the front foot but gets beaten on the inside edge and wears it high on the pads.
On a length but again slanting down the leg side. Kwena Maphaka shoulders arms at it.
On the hard length, again going down the leg. Kwena Maphaka lets it be.
On the back of a length, going down the leg. Kwena Maphaka leaves it alone to the keeper.
Wide! Digs it in short, slanting down the leg side from around the wicket. Kwena Maphaka lets it go. WIDED for height.
On the back of a length, outside off. Codi Yusuf hangs back and punches it to deep cover for one.
Bowls it on a short length, on the middle and off. Codi Yusuf rides the bounce and works it to mid on.
Floats it up, on off. Kwena Maphaka lunges forward and blocks it back to the bowler.
Short and around leg, dabbed down on the leg side by Kwena.
Tossed up and slower, outside leg. Codi Yusuf tucks it to square leg for one.
Floated up, on leg, Codi Yusuf pushes it to cover.
Slower and fuller, turning into the batter from off. Kwena Maphaka tucks it to the square leg region for one.

OUT! CLEANED HIM UP! End of a good knock from Keshav Maharaj! Wellington Masakadza comes from over the wicket and tosses it up, on a nagging length, around the line of the leg stump, Maharaj skips down the track but fails to get to the pitch of the ball. He still goes through with the shot but fails to connect. The ball sneaks past the inside edge and goes on to uproot the middle stump. South Africa lose their 9th wicket at a lead of 519.
Keshav Maharaj (c) b W Masakadza 51 (70b 4x4 1x6)
Slower and fuller, on off. Codi Yusuf lunges forward and blocks it.
Short and on middle, Codi works it to mid-wicket.
Shortish and on middle, Codi Yusuf rocks back and blocks it back to the bowler.
Full and at the stumps, Codi Yusuf clips it to square leg.
Fuller and on off. Codi Yusuf lunges forward and looks to defend, but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full and on off, blocked out by Yusuf.
On the pads, on a length, Codi Yusuf turns it through square leg for a single.
Full and around leg, Codi defends it off the front foot.

OUT! TIMBER! Finally a breakthrough for Zimbabwe as the partnership between Keshav and Bosch comes to an end! Wellington Masakadza bowls it on a fuller length and outside the leg stump. The ball pitches on the rough and turns sharply towards the leg stump and Corbin Bosch who gets down on one knee and looks to sweep but misses and the ball goes past his legs to rattle the leg stump. Corbin Bosch departs on 36 (41).
Corbin Bosch b W Masakadza 36 (41b 4x4 0x6)
Short and around leg, Maharaj flicks it through square leg for a single.
Shortish and on middle and leg. A bit of extra bounce on that one. Keshav Maharaj rocks back and blocks it back.
Short and around leg, Bosch jabs it wide of mid-wicket for a single. 350 comes up for South Africa and the lead is now 517 runs!
Fuller and slower, on middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj clips it to the short fine leg region.
Short and on off, Keshav Maharaj pats it down the deck.
A bit fuller and on the pads. Keshav Maharaj from the crease tucks it to square leg.

FIFTY FOR MAHARAJ! Short and darted down leg, Maharaj swivels and helps it to the right of the man at short fine leg for a couple of runs. There seems to be some confusion with the scoreboard at the ground, as there has been no celebration from Maharaj himself or any acknowledgement from his teammates on the balcony.
Fuller and drifting down the leg side. Corbin Bosch tucks it to the deep mid-wicket for a single.
Short and on off, Bosch punches it straight to cover.
Short and around leg, pushed back to the bowler by Maharaj.
Slows it down, full and on leg, blocked out.
Full and on leg, defended off the front foot.
FOUR! Gets it fine enough this time! Full and down leg again, Maharaj sweeps it fine to the right of the man at short fine leg for a boundary.
Floated up, down leg, Keshav Maharaj sweeps it straight to short fine leg.
Shortish and on middle. Corbin Bosch tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and off. Keshav Maharaj works it to point.
Shorter and outside off. Keshav Maharaj rocks back and punches it to the left of cover. The fielder at cover region runs behind it and keeps it to two.
Shortish and on the leg stump. Keshav Maharaj gets on the back foot and drives it wide of cover for a couple of runs.
Slower and fuller, on middle. Keshav Maharaj blocks it watchfully.
Tossed up and fuller, on off. Corbin Bosch tucks it to mid-wicket.
Shortish, turning into the batter. Bosch clips it to mid wicket.

A half-tracker, on off, Keshav Maharaj goes deep in the crease and slaps it down the ground to the left of long on. Tanaka Chivanga almost overruns the ball near the fence and loses his balance but does well to prevent the ball from going past him. Maharaj comes charging back for the second run. That will be TEA on Day 3!
Looped up, fuller and on off, Maharaj blocks it out off the front foot.
Sliding down leg, on a nagging length, Maharaj swivels and swats it to short fine leg.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Keshav Maharaj defends well.
Outside off, a bit short, left alone by Keshav.
Drops it short, on off, Keshav Maharaj goes back and pulls it to the right of long on for a couple of runs. South Africa's lead is now 501!

The ball is too full for the sweep and it sneaks under the bat to catch David on the crouched back thigh. Bedingham might have gotten away with one here!
Flatter and quicker, on middle, David Bedingham goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated up, attacking the front pad, David Bedingham gets his bat out in front to block.
Too straight, on the pads, short in length, Bedingham tucks it to the right of deep square leg for a couple of runs.
Slower and fuller, around leg, David eases it to deep backward square leg for a run.
Short and on middle, nudged to short mid-wicket.
Turning onto the pads, on a nagging length, helped down to deep fine leg for one by Mulder. The partnership between Wiaan Mulder and David Bedingham is now worth 50.
Fuller and on middle, clipped to short mid-wicket.
On middle and leg, on a nagging length, kept out on the leg side.
Short and on off, Mulder presses back to jab it to mid-wicket.
Drifting in, full and on middle, Mulder ekes out an inside edge on the defence. A single is taken as the ball rolls towards square leg.
Very full, on off, Mulder defends it well.
Shorter and on off, knocked off the back foot to long on for a single.
Turning away, full and on off, David Bedingham smothers the spin this time.
Floated up, on off, David is tentative to get on the front foot for the block. The ball spins away to catch the outer half of the bat and it dribbles to backward point.
Looped up, on the pads, Wiaan turns it through backward square leg for one.
On middle and leg, played off the back foot to short mid-wicket by David.
Flatter and around leg, Mulder clips it wide of backward square leg for one.
Tossed up, fuller and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket.
Short and a bit of turn into the pads, Mulder nudges it to mid-wicket.
Pushed through, on the shorter side, on off, Mulder rocks back and punches it past cover. Vincent Masekesa gives it a chase and cuts it off with a slide. Two runs taken.
FOUR! A gift and Wiaan Mulder accepts it gleefully! Low full toss, outside off, Mulder swings through and tonks it along the ground to the left of mid on.
Slower and tighter, on off, David Bedingham pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Fired onto the pads, David Bedingham sweeps this full ball fine of the man at deep backward square leg for a boundary. South Africa cross 100 and their lead is now 270!
Short and outside off, cut away to deep cover for a single.

SIX! Wiaan Mulder gets to his FIFTY in style! 2nd half-century of Wiaan's Test career and he will be keen to make this start count. Drags the length back does Wellington Masakadza, on middle. This is way too short and Mulder pummels it over mid-wicket for a six.
Loopy delivery, at the toes, Wiaan takes it on the full and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flat and short, on off, punched to cover by Mulder.
On a length, around off. Wiaan Mulder looks to defend it but gets off the inner half of the bat to mid-wicket for one.
Beautiful delivery from Tanaka Chivanga! Bowls it on a good length, outside off. Nipping away from the batter and Wiaan Mulder looks to play away from the body and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Hits the length hard and on off. Wiaan Mulder steers it to the gully fielder.
On the back of a length, on the pads. David Bedingham clips it to backward square leg for a single.
On the short length, on middle, and off. Wiaan Mulder works it to mid-wicket for one.
On a length, around off, nipping away from over the wicket. Wiaan Mulder blocks it to the mid off region.
SIX! Short and punished! Wellington Masakadza serves it on the shortish length, on the stumps. David Bedingham gets on the back foot and pulls it away over mid-wicket for a six.
Quicker and shorter, on the leg stump. Wiaan Mulder rocks back and pulls it to the deep square leg region for one.
Fuller and slower, on off. Wiaan Mulder prods forward and blocks it to the off side.
Slower and fuller, on off. Wiaan Mulder hangs back and defends it back to the bowler.
Shortish and on middle and off. David Bedingham rocks back and tucks it to square leg for one.
Fuller and drifting onto the pads. David Bedingham tucks it to the mid on region.
On a hard length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder shoulders arms at it.
This squares up Mulder as it nips away late, on a good length, on off, Wiaan manages to keep it out.
Full and on the off stump line. Wiaan Mulder prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length, around off. Wiaan Mulder left it alone.
On a length, on off. Wiaan Mulder lets it be.

FOUR! Top edge and over the keeper's head! Tanaka Chivanga starts the over with a well-directed short ball around the badge of the helmet. The ball rises onto the batter, and Wiaan Mulder looks to pull that one but gets a top edge which goes over the keeper's head for a boundary.
FOUR! A boundary to end the over! Wellington Masakadza bowls it on a shortish length and outside off. David Bedingham gets on the back foot and cuts it to the left of backward point for a boundary.
Tossed up and fuller, on the leg. David Bedingham tucks it to mid-wicket.

Ouch, that will hurt! Short and on off, David Bedingham slaps it hard and Prince Masvaure at silly point, fails to hop and evade the ball in time. The ball catches him on the right leg and Prince tries to shake off the pain. The two umpires check on him but Prince has a smile on his face, which is good to see.
Fuller and on off, tucked to square leg by David Bedingham.
Shortish and outside off. Wiaan Mulder rocks back and punches it to the cover region. The sweeper cover runs after it and keeps it to three.
Tossed up and fuller, on stumps. David Bedingham taps it to mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Thumped! Banged in short, outside off, this sits up to be hit. Wiaan Mulder stands tall and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

Edge but falls short! Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on hard length, outside off. The ball kicked off the deck, and Wiaan Mulder who looks to defend but gets an outside edge, which falls short of second slip.
On a good length, nipping away from outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off, David Bedingham works it to the cover region for one.

Another brilliant ball from the bowler! Bowls it on a hard length, on off. David Bedingham looks to defend but the ball nips away and goes past the outside edge. A loud appeal of caught behind, but the umpire stays unmoved.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! First wicket for Zimbabwe on Day 3! Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on a fuller length, angling into the batter from off stump line. Tony de Zorzi looks to block it but the ball kicks up a bit and catches the outside edge. The ball goes low toward the second slip, and Sean Williams stays low to take a good catch to remove Tony de Zorzi!

Speared in, full and on off, Wiaan Mulder defends it well.
On a nagging length, on off, stabbed down on the off side.
Tossed up, on middle, Wiaan Mulder blocks it off front foot.
Shortish, on off. Wiaan Mulder rocks back and cuts it wide of backward point for a couple of runs.
Slower and fuller, on off. Wiaan Mulder lunges forward to block but gets a leading edge to the backward point region.
Shortish, turning into the batter. Tony de Zorzi tucks it to mid-wicket off the back foot for one.
On a nagging length, moving away from off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Wiaan Mulder defends it back to the bowler.
On the back of a length, on off. A hint of away movement and Wiaan Mulder left it alone to the keeper.
Outside off, on a good length, Wiaan Mulder lets it be.
Drops the length shorter and outside off. Wiaan Mulder lets it be.
On a length, angling on the leg stump. Tony de Zorzi tucks it to deep backward square leg for a single.

FOUR! Nicely played! Bowls it on a fuller length and slower, on off. Wiaan Mulder gets on the front foot and drives it down the ground. The ball beats the mid on fielder to his left and races away for a boundary.
Shortish, on off. Wiaan Mulder punches it to cover.
Darted in, short and on off, Wiaan Mulder goes back to block.
Tossed up and on off. Wiaan Mulder lunged forward and blocks it.
Slower and fuller, on the stump. Tony de Zorzi clips it wide of mid-wicket for a single.

FOUR! A loosener to start the over! Wellington Masakadza serves it on the shorter length, turning into the batter from off stump. Tony de Zorzi rocks back and pulls it comfortably to the deep backward square leg region for a boundary.
Play and a miss! Bowls it on a good length, hint of away movement from the off stump. Wiaan Mulder goes for the drive but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On the hard length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder watchfully leaves it alone to the keeper.
Bowls around the sixth stump line, on good length. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
On good length, wide outside off from over the wicket. Wiaan Mulder lets it be.
Full and slanting down the leg side. Tony de Zorzi tucks it to the fine leg region for one.
On a fuller length, outside off from around the wicket. Tony de Zorzi leaves it alone.
Fuller and on off. Wiaan Mulder prods forward and blocks it to backward point.
Floats it up and on off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Slower and fuller, outside off. Wiaan Mulder lets it go.
50 up for South Africa! Gives a bit more air and fuller, on off. Tony de Zorzi drives it to mid off for a single.
Fuller and on middle and leg. Tony de Zorzi tucks it to short fine leg.
Tossed up and full, on the off stump. Tony de Zorzi clips it to the leg side.
BRAVE LEAVE! Blessing Muzarabani angles in a length ball, outside off. Mulder shoulders arms to it.
Well outside off, Mulder offers no shot.
Short in length and on middle, Mulder gets low and pulls it to short mid-wicket.
FOUR! HIT AWAY! Any width on offer and it's been punished! Blessing Muzarabani goes a bit short and outside off, Mulder cuts it past point for a boundary.
LOVELY! Blessing Muzarabani cuts out the width and gets close to the off pole, touch fuller. Mulder plants his front foot to defend but misses.
FOUR! Crunched! Blessing Muzarabani offers width outside off, on a length. Wiaan Mulder presses forward and punches it through covers and it rolls to the fence.
Gives a bit of width on this flighted delivery. Wiaan Mulder drives it to deep cover for a single.
A bit fuller and around off, comes with the arm. Wiaan Mulder blocks on the deck.
Skiddy length, fuller and on middle, Wiaan Mulder gets inside the line and dead bats it.
Tossed up on middle, Wiaan Mulder defends it out.
Floats it very full and around off, Mulder drops it to cover.
Flatter delivery on middle, Tony de Zorzi goes back and flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, drifting around middle and off. Mulder taps it to point. No run.
An inswinger pitched up, outside off. Mulder plays through the line but straight to point.
Tad fuller and around the fourth and fifth stump line. Mulder knocks it to cover.
FOUR! Soft hands from Mulder! Short in length and angling around off. Mulder looks to defend but deliberately plays with soft hands and edges it in between the slip cordon and gully for a boundary.
BEATEN! Short of a length and outside off, slight shape on this one. Mulder has a tentative push at it and misses.
A good length delivery, around off. Mulder defends with soft hands to the man at gully.
Drifting in from outside off, on a fullish length. Rather than committing on the front foot, Tony de Zorzi goes back and across to keep it out.
Slower and fuller, on off. Tony de Zorzi prods forward and looks to work it to the leg side but gets a thick leading edge to the gully region. Two runs taken.
Shortish, turning into the batter from off. Tony de Zorzi rocks back and clips it to short fine leg.
Floats it fuller, on the off. Tony de Zorzi drives it to short cover.
Full, sliding down the leg side. Tony de Zorzi leaves it alone.
On a fuller length, on off. Tony de Zorzi tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple runs. With that, South Africa's lead is 200 runs!
On the hard length, on the off stump. Wiaan Mulder rides the bounce and dabs it to gully.
Good length, on off. Wiaan Mulder shoulders arms at it.
Good length, around off stump. Wiaan Mulder shoulders arms at it.
BEATEN! On the back of a length, outside off. Bit of angling away from the batter and Wiaan Mulder shuffles across the off stump to defend, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder lets it be.
Back of a length, around off. Wiaan Mulder looks to punch but gets a thick inside edge onto his pad.

Fuller and slower, around the off. It lands and turns just a bit in. Tony de Zorzi gets forward to block but gets beaten on the inside edge and wears it on the front pad. A huge appeal of LBW, but the umpire turns it down. The impact just might have been outside off.
Fuller, on the stumps. Tony de Zorzi tucks it to short leg.
Tossed up, fuller and off. Wiaan Mulder lunges forward to defend but gets an inside edge to square leg for a single.
Slower and fuller, on the stumps. Wiaan Mulder drives it to mid on.
Shortish, around off. Wiaan Mulder rocks back and punches it to deep cover from the back foot for a couple of runs.
Fuller and turns into the batter, Tony de Zorzi gets on the back foot and tucks it to deep backward square leg for one.
On a length, around off. Mulder defends on the off side.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder tucks it towards mid-wicket.
On a good length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder looks poke it away from his body but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, around off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.

Good work in the deep! On the back of a length, on the off stump line. Tony de Zorzi rides the bounce and once again punches it to the cover region from the back foot. The fielder at the covers gives it a chase and just flicks the ball back with a diving effort. The third umpire is having a look at the save, and the decision is made as the fielder has done well to save a run. 3 runs taken.
On the back of a length, on the middle and leg from over the wicket. Wiaan Mulder clips it to deep backward square leg for a single.

FOUR! Solid punch from Tony! Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on the back of a length, angling into the batter. Tony de Zorzi rocks back on the back foot and punches it brilliantly through the cover region for a boundary.
Goes a bit fuller, just outside off. Tony de Zorzi defends it to the cover region.
Short length, outside off. Tony de Zorzi lets it be.
FOUR! Pulled away nicely! Tanaka Chivanga serves it on the short length, angling onto the pads. Tony de Zorzi gets on the back foot and pulls it away to the fine leg region for a boundary.
On the back of a length, on the off stump. Tony de Zorzi rides the bounce and blocks it to the off side.
Starts with a hard length, angling into the batter from around the wicket. Tony de Zorzi defends it to the short cover region.
Solid over from Blessing Muzarabani! Length delivery on middle, shaping away. Wiaan Mulder closes the bat face to flick, and gets a thick leading edge, but falls very short in front of the bowler.
Outside off, on a length and Wiaan Mulder shoulders arms to it.
Slants it full and on middle and leg, Tony de Zorzi whacks it behind square leg for a single.
Sticks to the same length and keeps it around off. Tony de Zorzi defends right under his eyes.
Blessing Muzarabani drags his length back and bowls it around off. Tony de Zorzi is cramped a bit as he blocks it on the deck.
Tad fuller and outside off. Tony de Zorzi leans and firmly punches it through covers for a couple of runs.
Drops it fuller and on middle, outward movement seen. Mulder whips it behind square leg where the fielder runs to his right, slides and saves a couple of runs.
An outswinger, fuller and outside off. Mulder happily leaves it.
FALLS SAFELY! Short in length and outside off. Mulder looks to pull but the extra bounce takes the top edge and flies to deep mid-wicket, in the vacant region for a couple.
Length ball, around middle. Wiaan Mulder solidly defends it out.
Tanaka Chivanga pushes it slightly fuller and just outside off. Mulder defends with soft hands and splices his shot to the fielder at gully, who picks up on a bounce.
Back of a length delivery, around off, Tony de Zorzi knocks it to the right of mid off for a single.
On a nagging length and on middle, Mulder nudges it straight to mid-wicket.

Ohh, that will sting! Prince Masvaure looks in pain and on the ground. Short in length and on middle, Mulder pulls it with some venom but hits it straight to short leg where Prince Masvaure gets hit just over his left knee, near the flap of the pads.
BEATEN! Into the surface, slightly short and angling on middle, Mulder presses forward to defend but gets hit high on the pads. The ball is doing its bit.

BEAUTY! Blessing Muzarabani turns and appeals with a bit of hope but the umpire turns it down. Slants in a good length delivery around off, it bounces and nips away as well. Mulder tries to defend inside the line but is well beaten.
Serves it short and outside off, wobble seam delivery. Mulder lets it go to the keeper.
Tony de Zorzi is off the mark! Bowls it on a length and on middle, Tony de Zorzi plays with the angle to square leg for a single.
Fuller delivery, shaping away, outside off. Mulder offers no shot to it.
Wide! Bowls the outswinger wide outside off. Mulder leaves it alone. The keeper collects in front of first slip. Wided.
Drops it short and well-directed on middle, Mulder pulls it straight to square leg.

FOUR! Strong shot from Mulder! Short of a length and outside off. Mulder punches off the back foot through point, in the vacant region and it races to the fence. He has done his job with the ball, now time to shine with the bat.
Tight from Tanaka Chivanga! Tad fuller and around off, angling in. Wiaan Mulder defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Tanaka Chivanga continues to shine in this game. Superb field placement! It went straight to the fielder! A good length delivery, around the sixth stump line, in the channel and Matthew Breetzke had to play at it. The ball lands and just straightens enough to find the thick outside edge. It carries flat and straight to Wessly Madhevere at gully. Bright start by Zimbabwe. An underwhelming outing for Matthew Breetzke again as he departs on 1 (6). South Africa are 1/1, leading by 168 runs.

Tanaka Chivanga steams in and serves it on a length and around off. Matthew Breetzke hangs back and defends it out.
Bowls in the same channel with the same intensity and the same length. Tony de Zorzi leans and defends on the off side.
Comes around the wicket to the left-hander, touch fuller and around the fourth stump line. Tony de Zorzi solidly blocks.
South Africa are underway! Makes the batter play for the first time! Short in length and around off, Matthew Breetzke hops and punches it to the right of cover for one.
Blessing Muzarabani generates the extra bounce but the line is non-troubling. Outside off, left alone.
Blessing Muzarabani serves it slightly short and outside off. Matthew Breetzke shoulders arms to it.
Fuller delivery, outside off and swings away. Matthew Breetzke shoulders arms to it.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND TAKEN! The last one bites the dust as Zimbabwe gets bundled out for 251 runs! Keshav Maharaj bowls it slower in the air and fuller, on off. Tanaka Chivanga clears his front leg and goes for a wild slog, but gets off the toe end of the bat towards long on. Kwena Maphaka from mid on runs backward and takes a good catch to end the Zimbabwe innings. South Africa gets a healthy lead of 167 runs.

Floats it up and slower, on the middle. Tanaka Chivanga defends it to the off side.
Fuller and slower, on the leg stump. Tanaka Chivanga blocks it back to the bowler.
Tossed up and on the pads. Vincent Masekesa clips it to deep backward square leg for a single.

OUT! BOWLED!  Wiaan Mulder has his 4th wicket of the innings as he knocks over Blessing Muzarabani! Wiaan Mulder pitches it on the good length, just around the fourth stump line. Blessing Muzarabani looks to work it to the off side but the ball straightens off the deck, and he gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball rattles the off stump. On the back of a length, just outside off. Blessing Muzarabani drives it to the mid off fielder.
On a hard length, on the middle and off. Blessing Muzarabani punches it to mid on from the back foot.
On a length, on the off stump. Blessing Muzarabani drives it to cover.
On the back of a length, on the middle and leg. Vincent Masekesa pulls it to the fine leg region for one. The 250 comes up for Zimbabwe!
Short length, angling down the leg side. Vincent Masekesa looks to pull but fails to get any connection.
Floats it up and off. Blessing Muzarabani lunges forward and blocks it to the off side.
Fuller and slower, on off. Blessing Muzarabani blocks that one off front foot.
Shortish, just around off. Blessing Muzarabani looks to block this one but bal spins away and goes past the outside edge.
Tossed up and fuller, turning away from around the wicket. Blessing Muzarabani looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.

OUT! STUMPED! End of a brilliant knock from Sean Williams! Probably looked a bit tired in this session. Tossed up, outside off and it turns away. Sean Williams takes a big stride forward to defend but misses as the ball turns away and goes past his outside edge. So big was the stride that Sean Williams failed to drag his back foot inside the line. Kyle Verreynne collects and clips the bails off. Easy decision for the third umpire. Zimbabwe in trouble now as Sean Williams departs for a marathon 137 (163).
