Shortish, angling into the batter. Sean Williams clips it to the mid-wicket region.

FOUR! That's nicely driven by Vincent Masekesa! Wiaan Mulder bowls it on a good length, just outside off. Vincent Masekesa plants his front foot forward and drives it nicely to the cover region for a boundary.
Goes fuller, just outside off. Vincent Masekesa leaves it alone to the keeper.
On the back of a length, angling onto the off stump. Vincent Masekesa rides the bounce and punches it to the cover region.
Drops his length back, on the outside off. Vincent Masekesa gets top on the bounce and steers it to backward point.
Goes fuller, on the off stump from over the wicket. Vincent Masekesa drives it to the cover fielder.
Starts from around the wicket, bowls it on a length, outside off. Sean Williams punches it to deep backward point for a single.
Short of a good length, cutting back into the batter. Vincent Masekesa sees the ball carry through to the keeper.
Length, around the leg stump line, nudged to short mid-wicket.

Gee, how has that missed the stumps? A nicely crafted delivery from Bosch! Fuller and nipping in off the deck. Vincent Masekesa plays over the line and the ball beats the inside edge. Passes scarily over the middle stump.
A steep bumper, on the bodyline, Vincent Masekesa finds himself in an awkward position to work that in the leg side. The ball hits the splice of the bat and rolls beside the pitch on the leg side.
Bangs it very hard on the deck, does Corbin, on top of middle and leg. Vincent Masekesa gets his body behind the line and punches it back to the bowler.
A yard behind fuller length, outside off, Sean Williams waits for it and cuts it through backward point for a single.
A bit too full, on middle, Vincent Masekesa pushes this out to short cover.
Same line, same length, Vincent Masekesa stabs it back to the bowler.
Good length, on off, Vincent Masekesa is solid in defence as he keeps it out.
Short-pitched delivery, on the fourth stump. Vincent Masekesa shoulders arms at it.
Tad full, on off, driven wide of mid off. Keshav Maharaj gets across and intercepts it.
Length-delivery, on middle, straightens up a bit with bounce. Vincent Masekesa gets squared to block it forward and is hit on the back thigh pad.
Fuller and around off, Vincent Masekesa presses forward and drives it through the cover region for a single.
Length ball, on middle, punched to the cover region.
Straight and full, on off, pushed firmly to short cover.

Short but angled down leg, Vincent Masekesa misses to flick and the ball grazes the front thigh pad before carrying to the keeper. There's a slight appeal for caught behind but wanes almost instantly.
Length, on off, defended out.

IN THE AIR...Lands safe. Short and at the shoulder height of the batter. Sean Williams miscues the pull shot. It goes off the top edge, but luckily for him, the ball lands well in front of the fielder at deep backward square leg. One taken. Williams continues to fight on for the Chevrons.
Back of a length, outside off, nibbling away. Vincent Masekesa goes fishing at it, away from the body and gets beaten.

Short delivery, on top of the stumps, Vincent Masekesa swivels and pulls this past the right of the diving square leg fielder. The ball slows on its way to the ropes as it is not timed that well. Kwena Maphaka runs across to the left and mops it off in the deep. Two taken.
Good length, aimed at the sticks. Vincent Masekesa blocks it straight back to the bowler.
Length, outside off, tapped out to the point region.
Whoa, a real tempter! This one angles in and then deviates away off the pitch, on a length, outside off. Vincent Masekesa goes poking at it and is beaten past the outside edge.
Half-tracker, outside off, steered away to deep backward point for a single.

That nip-backer which jags back in with some more bounce, on middle and leg. Vincent Masekesa gets on the front foot to defend, but the ball hits the splice of the bat and rolls beside the pitch on the leg side. Zimbabwe trail by 180 more runs.
Fuller and on off, Vincent Masekesa drives it straight back to the bowler.
Right in front of the sticks, Vincent Masekesa watchfully blocks this full ball into the leg side.
Angled onto the pads, on a fullish length. Vincent Masekesa misses to connect the flick shot and gets rammed on the front pad. Half and appeal for LBW, but dies down almost instantly.
Back of a length, on off, tapped wide of backward point for a single.

FOUR! Poor and punished! Sean is not going to miss those! Width offered, on a length. Sean Williams gets everything he wants - height, weight, and length. Leans on the back foot and plays the square cut through backward point for a boundary.

FOUR BYES! Goes through! Codi Yusuf angles this onto the pads, full in length, Vincent Masekesa misses to flick it in the leg side, and the ball brushes off the front pad. It goes to the left of the diving Kyle Verreynne and goes very fine to the deep fine leg fence.
Straight and speared on the off stump, Vincent Masekesa presses forward and presents a solid front foot defence to this full ball.
Outside off, good length, Sean Williams cuts it square to deep point for one.
Short of full, outside off, going straight on and keeping a bit low. Sean Williams tries to cut it from his crease and misses as the ball goes below the angled bat.
Back of a length, around off, Sean Williams punches it off the back foot to short cover.
Short and on off, Sean ducks under it.

Fired fuller and straight onto the pads, Sean Williams misses to flick it away and the ball thumps on the front pad before rolling into the square leg region. Tony de Zorzi from backward square leg runs to his right and stops it. Sean Williams, with some battle scars to show, limps a bit to cross over for a single.
Bangs it hard on the surface, angling on the leg stump. Vincent Masekesa jumps off the back foot and steers this through square leg for a single.
Short of a length, outside off, Vincent opts to leave.
Nagging length, but going down leg, Vincent Masekesa misses to glance off the back foot.
Cannoned fuller, at off, Sean Williams clears his front leg and knocks the ball through cover-point for a single.
Too short, outside leg, climbing over the batter. Sean ducks under it to let it pass.
In-between length, nips back in from outside off. Vincent Masekesa shows no interest in playing at it.

Oh, almost dragged on! Jags back in from outside off, on a length. Vincent Masekesa is cramped up for space and gets it off the inside edge of the bat as he tries to keep it out. The ball dribbles over the stumps and rolls behind.
Length, outside off, Vincent Masekesa opens the bat and glides it to the gully fielder.
Good-length delivery, outside off, Sean Williams dabs it to the cover-point region for a quick single.
Laser-straight on the middle stump, on a length, Vincent Masekesa gets across and tucks this to the left of mid-wicket for a single.
Oh, some extra bounce on this one. Short and outside off, Sean Williams climbs on the ball and cuts it off the outside edge to deep third for a single.
On the back of a length, on top of off and middle, angling in. Vincent Masekesa hops off and stabs it down to the surface.
Banged short and on the leg stump line, from around the wickets. Sean Williams controls the pull shot along the ground, and hits it to the left of Tony de Zorzi at short leg for a single.
Full and on the stumps, flicked to short mid-wicket.

FOUR! A shot of real authority! Shortish and outside off, Sean Williams stands tall, reads the length in a trice and pulls this through mid-wicket for a cracking boundary. Zimbabwe now trail by 197 runs.
Around off, pushed to mid off.

Half an appeal for LBW, but not given! A nip-backer from middle, on a good length. Sean Williams gets a bit too across to work that into the leg side, but misses and gets hit on the front pad. Possibly a bit too high and going down leg.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! CAUGHT BEHIND! Codi Yusuf gets his third wicket and continues to impress on his debut game! Spears it on a fullish length, from around the wickets. It lands and just straightens up a bit off the deck. Wellington Masakadza pushes forward to block it, but plays inside the line of the ball. A feather of an outside edge is found and Kyle Verreynne takes a regulation catch behind the sticks. Wellington Masakadza departs for 4 (23) and Zimbabwe are 217/7, trailing by 201 more runs.

Fuller now, on off, Wellington Masakadza prods forward and defends it out to cover.
Length, on the off pole, Wellington Masakadza knocks it to mid off.
That in-between length, on off, Wellington Masakadza gets on the back foot and punches it to the left of the backward point fielder who slides to intercept it.
Short and outside off, punched through cover for a single.

FOUR! A good start to the final session for the Chevrons! A half volley, on off, Sean Williams drives it straight down the ground for a boundary. Not quite convincing as it goes off the inside half of the bat. But, a boundary, nonetheless.
Hard length, going across the batter, on the leg stump line. Wellington Masakadza offers no shot. The ball deflects off the thigh pad and runs down to deep fine leg. And that will be TEA ON DAY 2!
Length ball, on off, punched to the off side.

EDGED, BUT DOES NOT CARRY! Straighter and fuller, outside off, Wellington Masakadza prods half forward to drive it straight, but gets a thick outside edge. The ball dips low in front of the second slip fielder who collects it on the bounce.
Short and wide of off, Sean Williams climbs on the bounce and cuts it over backward point for a single.
BEATEN AGAIN! Back of a length, nipping in a touch. Sean Williams stays leg side to slash it away, but misses to connect.

BEATEN! Touch full and in the corridor of uncertainty, making the batter play at it. Sean Williams without any foot movement, tries to defend it out, but misses and the ball passes just over the off pole.

Codi Yusuf continues to test the nerves of the batters! Good length, just outside off and then angles in with some bounce. Wellington Masakadza is squared up and looks to block off the back foot but gets the ball high on his gloves before it rolls to the gully region.
Nagging length, on off, tapped off the back foot to short cover.

Snorter! Speared in full and outside off, Wellington Masakadza gets forward to play at it, but the ball straightens off the pitch, and Wellington Masakadza, in time, pulls his bat away from the line of the ball to leave.
Hits the deck hard, on top of off, Wellington Masakadza with the back foot punch, eases into to the off side.
Short length, outside off, Sean Williams guides it late towards deep third for a single.
Uppish and through! Back of a length, outside off. Sean Williams plays it on the rise, but ends up chipping in uppishly, and between cover and mid off. Two taken.

That's a close leave! Touch full from Kwena Maphaka, and this one lands and jags back into the batter sharply. Wellington Masakadza prods forward and decides to shoulder arms at it. The ball, however, passes very close to that off pole.
Full and going down leg, Wellington Masakadza gets well inside the line to leave.
Nagging length, outside off, left alone by Wellington.
Spears in a low full toss, outside off, Wellington Masakadza plays with hard hands to drive through cover, but does not lay the bat on the ball. Misses.

This is cannoned straight on the stumps, full in length. Sean Williams is squared up and brings his bat in front to push it straight, but gets a thick leading edge that goes past backward point for a single.

Oh, goodness me! That's straight on the helmet! Maphaka is the bowler again! Bangs it hard on the surface, nipping back in quickly from off. Sean Williams is taken by surprise with that bounce and he does not get much cushion of time to sway away from the line of the ball. Tries for an evasive pull shot, but misses, and takes a big blow on the helmet. Good signs to see that he gives a little smile, gesturing he is okay. But the mandatory concussion will take place.
The line of attack remains on the stumps, but the length is full this time. Wellington Masakadza blocks it with a straight bat back to the bowler.
Bashes the length hard, on off, Wellington Masakadza gets inside the line and drops it on the pitch with soft hands.
Full, straight on, outside off, left alone by Masakadza.
Another one that slants back into the batter, on a length, Wellington Masakadza tries to work that across but plays over the wrong line. Gets an inside edge and is rapped high on the front pad.
This one nips back in on top of off, Wellington Masakadza hops across and nudges this with soft hands to the leg side.
Back of a length, around off, Sean Williams stays leg side and opens the bat face and guides it to the right of backward point for a single.

FOUR! Wonderful shot! Keshav drops a flighted ball, full and outside off, enough width for any batter to work with. Wellington Masakadza spreads all over the crease, extends his arms and smashes that through covers for a boundary. Perfect timing. Zimbabwe trail by 212 runs!
Floated fuller and on off, Wellington Masakadza leans on and taps it back to the bowler.
Nicely looped up, full and outside off, Wellington Masakadza gets low to slog it away, but toe ends it back to the bowler.
Maharaj pulls the length back a bit, around off, Sean Williams hangs back and punches it with the spin, through the vacant mid on region for a single.
Flat, quick, and full, Sean Williams clips this to short mid-wicket.
Pushed through, full and spinning in from off, Sean Williams with a gentle push back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wiaan Mulder gets his third of this innings as he bowls this one on a good length, on the middle. Tafadzwa Tsiga gets on the front foot and looks to flick that one on the leg side, but gets a leading edge to the backward point region. Codi Yusuf takes a regulation catch and Tafadzwa Tsiga departs on 9(8), and Zimbabwe are six down.

Back of a length, on the pads. Sean Williams flicks it to fine leg for a single.
FOUR! 200 up for Zimbabwe! Wiaan Mulder serves it on a short length, on the middle, and off. The ball kicks off the deck and Sean Williams guides it over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length, angling down the leg. Sean Williams looks to flick and misses it to the keeper.
Attacks the off pole, does Mulder, Sean Williams gets right behind the line and blocks it onto the pitch.
Good length, just around the fourth stump. Williams looks to drive on the rise, but the ball does not shoot up as much as Sean anticipated. He gets beaten as the ball passes close to the under edge.
Full, and drifting on the pads, Tsiga eases it to mid-wicket.
Fuller and slower. outside off. Tafadzwa Tsiga lunges forward and blocks it to the off side.
Fuller and on off, Sean Williams tucks it mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and around off. Tafadzwa Tsiga taps it to the left of cover for a quick single.
Tossed up and fuller, on the stumps. Tafadzwa Tsiga blocks it off the front foot.
Spins in from outside off, on a length, Sean Williams rocks back and cuts it through cover-point for a single.
Back of a length, around off stump. Tafadzwa Tsiga punches it to backward point.

EDGED AGAIN, FOUR MORE! Streaky, but Zimbabwe won't mind. Hard length, nibbling away from around off. Tsiga gets a bit squared up as he looks to defend off the back foot. Gets a thick, healthy outside edge that goes through the gap of the second slip and the gully fielder for a boundary.

OUTSIDE EDGE, FOUR! Tafadzwa Tsiga gets off the mark in an edgy fashion! Wiaan Mulder bowls it on a fuller length, around off. Tafadzwa Tsiga goes for a booming drive but gets a thick outside edge which goes wide of the fielder at the second slip. The ball runs away to the fence for a boundary.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Wiaan Mulder bowls it on a good length, outside off. Prince Masvaure looks to defend off the front foot but gets a thick outside edge. Kyle Verreynne, behind the wicket, dives to his left to take a low catch. An appeal for caught behind, but the umpire is not convinced, so they send it upstairs! The third umpire first checks for the legality of the delivery. No issues there as some part of Mulder's boot is behind the line. Now, the third umpire is checking for a fair catch. A few angles pop up and it is deemed a clean catch. OUT is displayed on the big screen as Kyle Verreynne just scooped the ball before the grass cleanly. Prince Masvaure departs on 7 (9) and Zimbabwe are five down!

HUNDRED FOR SEAN WILLIAMS! An outstanding innings from the veteran as he gets himself to his 6th Test century! Entire Queens Sports Club in Bulawayo gets aloft to appreciate this special knock from a special player. This is a length-delivery, on off, skidding through the surface and arriving very quickly on the batter. Sean Williams, however, lets the ball arrive at him and pulls this to deep square leg.  He makes his ground to the other end, takes off the helmet, and lifts it skyward, soaking up the applause echoing around the ground. Came in to bat when Zimbabwe were struggling at 23/2, formed a crucial 91-run stand with Ervine and hasn't looked back since he got off to his fifty. Has batted with a positive intent and has managed to pull Zimbabwe out of a deeper trouble.
Good length, on off from around the wicket. Sean Williams prods forward and drives it to the cover region. The fielder from the backward point runs across and keeps it to two. Sean moves to 99!
Slower and fuller, around off. Sean Williams skips down the track and looks to go down the ground but gets an inside half of the bat to long on for a single.
Slower and fuller, outside off. Sean Williams gets on the frot foot and works it with the inner half of the bat to mid-wicket.
Fuller, on off. Sean Williams blocks it off the back foot.

FOUR! Nicely driven by Sean! Keshav Maharaj tossed it up fuller and wide outside off. Sean Williams sees the width and lunges forward to drive it to cover for a boundary. He moves to 96 with that boundary.

Tossed up and fuller, on the middle and off. Sean Williams drives it to the left of the bowler. Keshav Maharaj puts in a diving effort on his follow-through to stop the ball, but as his left hand scrapes along the surface, he appears to be in a bit of discomfort. It seems his fingers may have rolled over the ball before making contact with the turf.

Fuller, on the stumps. Prince Masvaure gets on the front foot and drives it to short mid-wicket. The fielder dives to his right and gets his hands onto it, but the batters run a single in the meantime.
Good length, on the middle and off. Sean Williams drives it to cover.
On a length, on off. Prince Masvaure clips it to mid-wicket for one.
On a nagging length, angling onto the leg stump. Sean Williams tucks it to deep backward square leg for one.
On a length, angling onto the pads. Prince Masvaure clips it to the fine leg. The fielder there runs to his left and keeps it to one.
On a good length, outside off. Prince Masvaure blocks it to mid on.
Fuller and outside off. Sean Williams rocks back and works it to backward point for one.
Tossed up and fuller, on off. Sean Williams drives it to long on for one. He moves into 90s!
Fuller, outside off, Sean Williams drives it back to the bowler.
Floats it fuller and on off. Sean Williams prods forward and blocks it.
Fuller, and on the middle and off. Prince Masvaure taps it to square leg for one.
Slower and turning into the batter. Prince Masvaure clips it to short leg.
Bowls it fuller and on the off stump. Prince Masvaure gets on the front foot and drives it nicely to the cover region for two.
Bowls it on a good length, on the off stump. Prince Masvaure looks to shoulders arms at it but gets an inside edge to the deep third for a single. He gets off the mark in a streaky manner.

OUT! LBW! South Africa get a breakthrough here, and a good partnership between these two batters comes to an end. Wiaan Mulder bowls it on a full length, nipping back onto the off stump. Wessly Madhevere plants his front foot forward and looks to flick it from the crease, but plays over the wrong line and misses it, and wears it on the front pad. A huge shot of LBW and up goes the finger of the umpire. Wessly Madhevere departs on 15 (25). Zimbabwe are 167/4, trailing by 251 runs.

Back of a length, outside off. Wessly Madhevere blocks it off the back foot.
Hits the deck hard, on top of off, Wessly Madhevere meets the ball right under his eyes and blocks it solidly on the pitch.
Short and outside off. Wessly Madhevere blocks it to cover off back foot.
Length-delivery, just outside off, Sean Williams pins it with a cut shot towards deep cover for a single.
Slower and fuller, on the stumps. Sean Williams sweeps it to backward square leg for one.

Ooooh! Prodigious turn! Lands around off and turns sharply back in. Sean Williams is cramped up for room and goes back and across, and looks to work it across to the leg side, but plays all over it and gets rapped on the front pad.
Full, on the off stump, Sean Williams punches it to point.
Fuller, on the off stump. Sean Williams sweeps it to deep backward square for a couple of runs.
Slower and fuller, on off. Sean Williams drives it to mid off.
FOUR! Sean Williams is scoring runs thick and fast! Keshav Maharaj floats it fuller and on the stumps. Sean Williams comes down the track and smashes it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Top delivery to end the over! Bowls it on a good length, in the off stump. Wessly Madhevere looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, wide outside off. Wessly Madhevere throws his hands at it but fails to connect.
Good length, nipping back on the off. Sean Williams taps it to the point for one.
On a nagging length, on the off stump. Sean Williams blocks it off front foot.

On a good length, angling onto the pads. Sean Williams looks to play across and clip it but misses, and wears it on the thigh pad. A huge appeal of LBW from the keeper but the umpire shakes his head in denial. Might be going down the leg side.
Full, outside off. Sean Williams drives it to mid off.
Wide! Starts from around the wicket, dugs it short of a length and it goes over Sean Williams' helmet. WIDED!

THREE RUNS! He has a habit of playing these one-handed sweeps! Tossed up, outside off, Sean Williams hits it to deep square leg. The fielder runs to his left, dives neatly near the fence and saves a run.
A bit too full and around off. Sean Williams defends on the front foot.
Tosses up a fuller delivery, outside off. Sean Williams knocks it to point.
Floated full and on off, eased to long off for a single.
The one that comes with the arm, length ball on leg. Wessly Madhevere goes back and blocks it hurriedly.
A juicy fuller delivery, outside off, invites Wessly Madhevere to defend but the ball spins away and goes past his outside edge.
Bowls it on the pads. Wessly Madhevere tucks it to deep square leg and keeps the strike.
BEAUTY! Wiaan Mulder bowls on a deceptive length, outside off, it nips away. Wessly Madhevere throws his bat at it but fails to connect.
Pitches it up and bowls it outside off. Wessly Madhevere nicely pushes it but straight to mid off.
Tad fuller and around off, Wessly Madhevere gets low to defend it back to Mulder.
Hard length delivery, around off, Sean Williams makes room and plays it through point for a run.
Short of a length and close to the off pole. Sean Williams stays behind the line to defend.
Tossed up, outside off. Wessly Madhevere plants his front foot out and defends it to point.
Flatter delivery, outside off, Sean Williams strokes it to point and rotates the strike.
Ohh, lovely! Keshav Maharaj slows it up, bowls it full and around off, not much turn. Sean Williams is drawn to defend but is beaten. Not far away from the off pole as it goes straight on.
FOUR! Half-a-chance! Sean Williams again skips down, hits this full toss, straight down past Maharaj's right hand and into the long off fence. The 150 is up for Zimbabwe!
Sean Williams now stays back and nudges this full ball to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Sean Williams has changed gears! He takes the charge and takes it on the full, whacks this full toss over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Most runs for Sean Williams have come in this region! Outside off, Sean Williams drops it past point for a single.
A skiddy length delivery, around off. Sean Williams watchfully blocks it out.
Touch fuller and on middle, Sean Williams hits it down to short mid on.
Corbin Bosch drags his length back by centimeters and bowls it outside off. Sean Williams on his toes, looks to cut but misses.
Much profound shot! On a nagging length and well outside off. Sean Williams punches it firmly past point for a couple.
FOUR! Zimbabwe are taking their chances! Short in length and outside off. Sean Williams toe ends his cut shot over the man at gully, well over for a boundary.
SIX! Pressure-releasing shot! Very full from Keshav Maharaj on middle, in the slot for someone like Wessly Madhevere, who slogs it over cow corner for a six.
Tossed up on middle, defended out.
What was that? Slants in a length ball, around off, it spins away and shoots up as well. Wessly Madhevere is surprised by the bounce as he leaves.
Very full and on middle, Wessly Madhevere eases it to mid on for a run.

Risky single! Wessly Madhevere apologises to Sean Williams for it as well. Slows this fuller delivery on off, Wessly Madhevere pushes it to mid off and takes off. Sean Williams is ball-watching and is late to rush across, but he makes his end before the mid off fielder releases a flat throw and scores a direct hit at the batting end.
Flights it full and on leg, straightens up. Wessly Madhevere prods and dead bats it.

Corbin Bosch comes around the wicket for the final delivery, bowls it on a length and outside off. Sean Williams hangs inside the crease to push it away but plays off the inner half of the bat around the corner.
Drops it short and outside off. Sean Williams cuts on the up and to deep point for a couple more.
THREE RUNS! That's some serious running! Angles in a length ball on middle, Wessly Madhevere flicks it past square leg. Till the time the fielder fetches it up, they take three runs.
Well bowled and well defended! On a good length and on middle, Wessly Madhevere blocks it on the leg side.
Spills it full and angling down the leg side. Wessly Madhevere looks to flick but misses.
Corbin Bosch bends his back and bowls it short and on middle. Wessly Madhevere defends with a straight bat.
Flatter delivery on middle, Wessly Madhevere goes back and works it to mid-wicket for a single.

JUST PAST SLIP! Floated full, around off, it lands and zips a bit. Wessly Madhevere puts a big stride forward to defend but slices it past slip and to third man for a couple. Streaky way to get off the mark.

OUT! STUMPED! Was that needed? Craig Ervine was batting so well from his crease, but to negotiate the spin, he came down the track. Keshav Maharaj nicely tosses it up, outside off. Craig Ervine fails to get his bat across and it goes past his blade to the keeper, Kyle Verreynne, who misses the stumps on his first attempt but quickly dislodges the bail. Well outside off, Craig Ervine offers no shot.

WIDES! Steams in and bowls a bumper on middle, too short and Craig Ervine leaves for a wide.

Generates some extra bounce again, outside off. Craig Ervine plays off the back foot through covers for easy couple.
In the outside off region, Craig Ervine has nothing to do with it.
Bowls it on the shorter side with some extra bounce, outside off. Craig Ervine punches it square on the off side for a brace.
Darted on the pads. Sean Williams flicks it to deep square leg, in the gap for a couple of runs.
Keshav Maharaj pushes it full and shifts his line just outside off. Sean Williams drags his sweep shot straight to square leg.
FOUR! Sean Williams piles his confidence with this shot! Looped up full and on off, this is slog-swept over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up, full and on middle, drilled to long on for a single.
Goes full and floats it around off. Craig Ervine prods and defends on the deck.
Flighted full and outside off, Craig Ervine leans and pushes it to mid off.
Too full and drifting on the pads. Craig Ervine flicks it to deep square leg and retains the strike.

And that will help! TEST FIFTY NUMBER 7 FOR THE VETERAN! Length ball, outside off. Sean Williams drops it to cover and moves to the other side. Came in at a difficult stage and has played well so far, forming a steadying partnership with his skipper.
BEATEN! Sean Williams is yet to pick up the pace of the game. He is too slow right now! Short in length and around off, nips in. Sean Williams tries tot defend inside the line and is beaten.
BEAMER! Sean Williams didn't see that coming! On a hard length and shaping on middle, Sean Williams is taken by surprise by the inward movement, he tries to fend it away but gets hit on the body.
Kwena Maphaka offers width again and drops it on the shorter side. Sean Williams tries to cut on the up but bottom edges it to the keeper who picks up off the deck.
Kwena Maphaka has started this session well! Short in length and outside off, Sean Williams dabs it low to the right of gully, who dives and stops on a bounce.

'CATCH IT' is the call from Keshav, but it is DROPPED! A tough, tough chance though. Keshav lands this full and gets a good bit of turn into the batter from outside off. Sean Williams premeditates to play the sweep shot but gets it off the glove due to that extra bounce. The ball just does a bit too much to spin sharply in and one hand comes off the bat as the ball lobs over the short leg region. The man from the first slip is a bit late to react and goes after it, diving across. Gets his hands on the ball, but eventually shells it down. The batters pinch in a quick single. There's no signal from the umpire for a leg bye, so it seems that it indeed did came off the glove. Okay, the replay shows that the ball brushed the forearm of Williams before lobbing behind. 100 IS UP FOR ZIMBABWE. They trail by 318 runs.

Short of full, outside off, tapped out on the off side.

Speared fuller and outside off, Craig Ervine prods forward and watches the ball go all the way through to the keeper.
Pitched halfway on the pitch, outside off, Sean Williams rises with the bounce and cuts it square to deep point for a single.
Short and straight, outside off, Sean Williams offers no shot at it.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, with some bounce outside off, Sean Williams shapes up to cut it square on the off side, but misses and the ball passes over his angled bat.
A well-directed bumper, around off which further climbs on the batter. Sean Williams sways away by arching back and lets it be.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Ervine works it to deep backward square leg for a single.

An appeal for LBW, but not entertained. Length, just outside off and spinning in with a drift. Ervine stands tall to work it across in the leg side, but gets an inside edge onto the thigh pad and the ball rolls to the off side, just near the strip for a single.
Full again, around off, Ervine prods forward to defend it back to the bowler.
Pushed through, full and just outside off, Craig Ervine blocks it out.
Nice and full, on middle, clipped to the leg side.

Over the stumps, full and on off, Craig Ervine leans forward and defends.
Good length, bouncing a bit over the top of off. Sean Williams opens up his body to stab it down the pitch. Zimbabwe trail by 324 runs and that will be LUNCH ON DAY 2!
FOUR! Just over! A bit too short and outside off, with that excessive bounce. Sean Williams hops on the toes and cuts it off the outside edge, over the gully fielder for a boundary.
Good length, on the leg stump, Craig Ervine pins it behind square to deep fine leg for a single.
Shortish delivery, slanted across the batter, on the leg stump. Craig Ervine tries to steer it into the leg ide, but the ball grazes off the thigh pad to square leg.
Nice change of lengths from Codi! Well-directed bumper, going over the batter's helmet. Craig Ervine dodges this by ducking under it.
On that fourth stump line, on a length, Craig Ervine lets the ball arrive and blocks it right under his eyes.
Tossed up, full and around off. Williams pushes this to cover.
Goes full and on off, Craig Ervine presses forward and opens the bat face. The ball rolls into the point region for a quick single.
Spins in from off, on a fuller length, Craig Ervine leans on and steers it with soft hands into the leg side, beside the pitch.
Looped up, on off, Craig Ervine eases this full ball to silly mid on.
Darted in fuller, on off, clipped straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and on off, Sean Williams skips forward and heaves it across to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Spears it fuller, around off. Craig Ervine does not quite commit fully on the front foot and pushes it off the inner half of the bat to mid on.
Good length, at off, Craig Ervine lets the ball arrive and taps it with soft hands to the off side.

Constantly causing problems for the batters! Hard length, angling in on middle. Craig Ervine looks to nudge it across but misses on the inside edge and the ball deflects off his body, and rolls behind.
Nicely crafted delivery! Outside off, springing off the deck on a good length. Craig Ervine keeps his bat inside the line of the ball to let it through.

Bangs the surface really hard, does Yusuf, on a length, slanting in on off, with some lift off the deck. Craig Ervine is squared up and just manages to fend it back in front of the second slip fielder.
Codi makes the batter play at it as he goes full and on the fourth stump. Craig Ervine with barely any footwork, tries to push it straight, but misses as the ball nibbles away.
Tossed up, around off. Williams defends it towards the silly point region.

Some turn! Pitches on a fuller length, around off. It lands, bounces and turns across and into the batter, going down the leg side. Sean Williams keeps his bat inside the line and Kyle Verreynne moves to his right to collect the ball.
Flighted full, on off, blocked straight back.
Full ball, pushed back to the bowler.

Well bowled! Williams is going nowhere as the umpire's finger stays down on the appeal. Keshav floats it up, full and outside off. It lands and turns sharply back into the batter, getting some bite. Sean Williams prods forward to defend, but misses as the ball passes close to the outside edge. It bounces off the surface and Kyle Verreynne has to hop a bit to collect the ball behind the wickets. Now, the question is whether Williams dragged his back leg back into the popping crease. And the side-on replay shows that Sean has just about managed to drag his foot back inside the line before Verreynne stretches his left hand ahead to dislodge the bail. However, the other side-on angle shows that the boot might be on the line, but with the shadow in the way, there's no conclusive evidence and the benefit of the doubt goes in favor of the batter.
Flighted fuller, outside off, Craig Ervine leans on and works this with the spin to long on for a single.

Ouch! That must have hurt! Yusuf targets the bodyline of the batter, and bashes the length hard by bending his back. The ball kisses the surface and rises up a bit, cramping Sean Williams for space to work with. He tries to drop it down the pitch, but takes a blow around his chest area.
Hits the deck hard, outside off, Sean Williams cuts it in front of square on the off side and hares back for the second run. Nice running.
Length, on off, punched into the off side. Oh, dear! Codi has overstepped and No Ball is signalled.

Yusuf seems to be bowling on a completely different surface. Two half chances in the same over! Generates that steep bounce again, around off, Craig Ervine brings his bat in front to dab it away into the off side, but the ball flies off the leading edge and goes to the left of the diving gully fielder for a single.
FOUR! Clipped away! Back of a length, angling in on off, Craig Ervine hops on the back foot and glances it through the square leg region for a boundary.
Good length and just around off. Ervine looks to defend off the front foot but is beaten on the outside edge.

IN THE AIR... LANDS SAFE! Short of a length, lifts off the deck around off. Sean Williams gets into an awkward position as he tries to wrist it into the leg side, but gets a leading edge that flies over the right of the keeper. However, luckily for him, the ball lands between backward square leg and short fine leg as the batters cross for a single.
Pushed through, too full and on off, Sean Williams clips this all along the turf to long on for one more.
Nice and full, outside off, carved out back to the bowler.
Action replay of the previous delivery. A single again.
Same line, same length, worked down to long on for a single.
Tossed up around off. Ervine clips it down to long on for a single.
Starts off with a knee-length full toss, on off, Sean Williams drags this to long on for a single.

Keeps the line of attack outside off, on a length, Sean Williams stands tall, opens the bat face and punches this past backward point for a single. The partnership moves on to 46 runs, as Zimbabwe trail by 346 runs.
Full on off, blocked out.
Nagging length, outside off, Sean Williams bunts it down the pitch. Yusuf is extracting that bounce off the deck which is pegging the batters to get on their toes.

Quick tap and run! Hard length, just outside off with some extra lift off the deck. Craig Ervine is taken aback by that excessive lift and drops his wrists to dab it beside the pitch on the off side. Sniffs a single as the gully fielder rushes in front to collect the ball and they cross over for one.
Good length, on middle, Craig Ervine tucks it across to mid on.

PEACH! Asks questions straightaway, does the debutant! Bowls from a wider angle, around the wickets, full and angling in and around off, Craig Ervine strides across to block, but the ball flirts past his outside edge.
On a good length, nipping back onto the pads. Sean Williams clips it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Sean Williams blocks it to the leg side.
On the back of a length, outside off. Sean Williams gets on the back foot and works it to the left of backward point. Two runs taken.
Drags his length back, on the off stump. Sean Williams rocks back and punches it to cover.
On a fuller length, on off. Sean Williams drives it nicely but straight to the cover fielder.

FOUR! Good timing on that one! Wiaan Mulder serves it on the back of a length, outside off. Sean Williams rises with the bounce and solidly punches it to the left of backward point for a boundary. The partnership grows to 40 now.
On a nagging length, around off. Craig Ervine defends it to the off side.
On a hard length, on off. Craig Ervine blocks it to backward point.

FOUR! Nicely cut away! Corbin Bosch bowls it on a short length, outside off. Craig Ervine rides the bounce and gets on the back foot and cuts it to the right of point. The fielder at point dives to his right, but is unable to stop it from racing away for a boundary.
On a length, just outside off. Craig Ervine prods forward and blocks it to the off side.
Goes fuller, on the middle and off. Craig Ervine blocks it back to the bowler.
Dugs in short from over the wicket, on the leg stump line. Craig Ervine ducks underneath it.
On a full length, on the middle and leg. Sean Williams flicks this to the left of mid on for a couple of quick runs.
On a hard length, on the stumps. Craig Ervine clips it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Nice delivery from Wiaan Mulder! Bowls it on a length, just outside off. Craig Ervine gets forward to defend it but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball straightens off the pitch.
On a good length, around off. Craig Ervine prods forward and punches it down the ground. The fielder from the mid on gives it a chase and keeps it to two.
On a length, on the off stump. Craig Ervine gets on the front foot and blocks it.
Bowls it on a good length, on middle and leg. Sean Williams rocks back and works it to mid on for one.
On the back of a length, on the stumps. Craig Ervine rocks back and blocks it back.
Comes from over the wicket and bowls it on a hard length, on the pads. Craig Ervine looks to clip it but misses it and wears on the thigh pad.
On a good length, just outside off. Craig Ervine blocks it off the front foot.
On a hard length, on the off stump. Craig Ervine cuts it to point.

Good running! Corbin Bosch bowls it on the back of a length, on the off stump. Sean Williams rides the bounce and punches it to the deep point region. The fielder from the backward point region gives it a long chase and keeps it to three!
Bowls it on a good length, outside off. Sean Williams throws his hands to slash it through the point region, but misses it on the outside edge.
On a length, on middle and leg. Craig Ervine clips it to the square leg.
On a full length, on the fifth stump line. Craig Ervine lunges forward and blocks it to the off side.
Bowls it on a touch fuller length, on the off stump. Craig Ervine prods forward and blocks it to the leg side.
On a good length, just around off. Craig Ervine blocks it right under his eyes.
On a hard length, angling onto the pads. Sean Williams tucks it to fine leg for one.
Back of a length, outside off from around the wicket. Sean Williams punches it to cover.
Bends his back and bowls it on the short of a length, outside off. Craig Ervine lets it be.
Drags the length back nd bowls it shorter. Craig Ervine ducks underneath it.
On a hard length, nipping back into the batter. Craig Ervine looks to clip it to the leg side but misses and wears on the thigh pad.
Swing and a miss! Corbin Bosch bowls it on a fuller length, wide outside off. Craig Ervine sees the width and throws his hands to it but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a good length, angling into the batter. Craig Ervine blocks it nicely to the off side.
On a hard length, angling onto the off stump from around the wicket. Craig Ervine defends it just behind the off stump.
Pitches it a bit fuller, on the off stump. Sean Williams gets inside the line and defends it back to the bowler.
On a nagging length, on the off stump. Sean Williams blocks it right under his eyes.
On the back of a length, on the off stump. Sean Williams works it to cover.
On a length, angling onto the leg stump. Sean Williams tucks it to the leg side from the back foot.
On a good length, on the middle and leg. Sean Williams clips it to mid-wicket.
Starts from around the wicket, bowls it on a good length, angling into the batter. Sean Williams shoulders arms at it.
Full length, outsdie off. Craig Ervine leaves it alone to the keeper.
Drags his length back, outside off. Craig Ervine gets on top of the bounce and cuts it straight to the point fielder.
On a naggign length, outside off. Craig Ervine left it alone.
Good length, angling away, left alone by Craig Ervine.
Short and wide outsdie off. Craig Ervine cuts it nicely, but straight to the point fielder.

FOUR! Craig Ervine welcomes Corbin Bosch with a boundary! Corbin Bosch starts off with a loosener, and bowls it on a short of a length, outside off. Craig Ervine sees the width and opens his arms to cut through point for a boundary. Zimbabwe trail by 368 runs as the 50 is up for the hosts.
On short length, on the leg, Craig Ervine tucks it to square leg for one.
On a good, angling across, Craig Ervine punches it straight to the point fielder.
BEATEN! Wiaan Mulder adjusts his length and bowls this one on a fuller side, just around the off stump. Craig Ervine gets on the front foot and looks to block, but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a back of a length, angling on middle and leg. Craig Ervine clips it behind the square on the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Craig Ervine lets it be.
Short and on off, Craig Ervine blocks it back to the bowler.
Good length, on the leg stump, Craig Ervine taps it to square leg for one.
On a good length, around off, Craig Ervine comes forward and block it.
BEATEN! On a good length, angling away from the batter. Craig Ervine looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge as the ball deviates away a shy bit.

On the back of a length, on the leg stump. Craig Ervine looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses it and wears it high on the thigh pad as the ball springs off the deck. Ervine looks in a bit of pain, but doesn't show much. Does a half-squat and continues.
On a length, angling into middle and off. Craig Ervine works it to mid-wicket.
Starts from around the wicket, pitches it on the back of a length, on the off stump. Sean Williams rides the bounce and helps it to the cover for a single.
Kwena Maphaka ends with a dot! Touch fuller and outside off, width on offer. Craig Ervine lets it go.
Darted on the pads, fuller length and Sean Williams nudges it to deep square leg for a run.
FOUR! Helped away! Maybe, Kwena Maphaka needs a break from this spell! Tad short and angling on the hips. Sean Williams gets low and pulls it in front of square on the leg side for a  single.
Sticks to the same length, outside off. Sean Williams knocks it to point.

FOUR! Authoritative shot! Short of a length delivery, outside off. Sean Williams gets on top of the bounce and slaps it past point for a boundary. It's important for Zimbabwe to keep scoring runs regularly and not get into a shell.
Kwena Maphaka goes full and outside off. Sean Williams punches it to cover.

How has that gone through? A delivery out of top drawer from the debutant. Craig Ervine is squared up here. Pushes in a length ball on off, it lands and jags back in, bit of extra bounce as well. Craig Ervine prods to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and it rolls over just past the off pole. Half an appeal for caught behind, but the umpire is unmoved.
Goes full and on middle and leg, Craig Ervine flicks it to square leg.
BEATEN! LOVELY! Shapes away a length ball, around the fifth stump line. Craig Ervine had to play it, leans to defend across but is beaten.
In the channel, around off and on a length. Craig Ervine punches it to cover.
Bowls it into the surface on the shorter side, around off. Craig Ervine gets tall and shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length and on the hips, Sean Williams helps it fine on the leg side for a single.

Leg bye! An appeal for LBW but just drifting down leg! Kwena Maphaka bowls an inswinger to the left-hander, this is full and on middle and leg. Sean Williams is pinged on the back foot as he tries to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. It rolls to the leg side for a leg bye.
FOUR! Second boundary of the over! Sean Williams just gives the direction as he pulls this short ball to square leg and bags a boundary.
Around off, on a length, Sean Williams punches it right off the middle of the blade but to cover.
Keeps it short and changes his line, bowls it down leg. Sean Williams looks to pull but is beaten. Good catch by the keeper, Kyle Verreynne to his right.
Kwena Maphaka offers width and bowls it on the shorter side. Sean Williams swings his blade and misses.

FOUR! Well played! Kwena Maphaka pushes it full and outside the channel, outside off. Sean Williams punches it past the man at gully, who dives to his left but it rolls past his stretched left hand and it rolls to the fence.
Just a run off the over! Codi Yusuf bangs it short and on middle, Brian Bennett ducks under it.
Goes short and slides it down the leg side. Brian Bennett looks to clip it away but misses.
An in-angler around off, on a length. Brian Bennett gets inside the line and defends it.
Sean Williams is underway! Tad fuller and around off, Sean Williams goes back and plays it to covers for a run.
On a good length and around the fifth stump line. Sean Williams tries to push but plays a false shot back to the bowler.
Drifts away a length ball, outside off, well outside the line and Sean Williams offers no shot.

Kwena Maphaka is not letting the batters settle in. Goes short this time and directs it onto the body. Brian Bennett gets his eyes off as he tries to pull and gets hit on the helmet. A mandatory concussion protocol to take place. The physio is out doing his job.
TOP NUT! Kwena Maphaka dishes out a yorker, straight line on the leg pole. Brian Bennett equally does well to dig it out.
Gets a bit of width and bowls it outside off. Brian Bennett punches with hard hands and plays it straight to point.
On a nagging length and makes the batter play as Kwena Maphaka bowls around off. Brian Bennett defends well.
BEATEN! Tentative push and beaten! Good length delivery, on middle and off, zips away off the deck. Brian Bennett tries to play with an angled bat but misses it.
Kwena Maphaka dishes in a fuller delivery on middle, Brian Bennett flicks it straight to square leg.
Wicket-maiden over by Codi Yusuf! Goes a bit full and around off, it is knocked to cover.
BEAUTY! Such lovely stuff from Codi Yusuf so far! Steams in and lands around off, it shapes across the batter. Sean Williams gets tall to push but misses it.
SWING AND A MISS! Short in length and outside off, it lands and jags away sharply. Sean Williams looks to push it away but is well beaten.
Codi Yusuf drags his length back and bowls it around off. Sean Williams drops it to the man at cover.
Bowls it full and wide outside off. Sean Williams covers his stumps and leaves it alone.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Codi Yusuf strikes again! He is playing with the pitch, extracting good pace and bounce, and that is what's giving him the results. Codi Yusuf bowls it slightly short and into the surface, it nips away from outside off. Nick Welch slashes hard at it, playing it away from the body, without any footwork. Ends up getting a faint outside edge to the keeper, Kyle Verreynne, who makes no mistake. Ordinary shot from Welch and he has to go on 4 (5). Zimbabwe are 23/2, trailing by 395 runs.
Nick Welch c K Verreynne b C Yusuf 4 (5b 1x4 0x6)
Targets the stumps this time! A good-length delivery, on leg, Brian Bennett tucks it with soft hands to the man at short leg.
Serves it full and outside off, well across the batter. Brian Bennett shoulders arms to it.
Shapes across a fuller delivery, outside off, Brian Bennett offers no shot to it.

FOUR! Solid shot! Fourth boundary for Brian Bennett already! Kwena Maphaka bangs it short and around off, close to the body but Brian Bennett gets into the position quickly as he punches it past cover and it rolls to the fence.
Kwena Maphaka needs to stick to this length and line! Angles across a length ball, outside off. Brian Bennett watchfully leaves it.
Kwena Maphaka errs in line and serves it well down leg. Brian Bennett lets it go to the keeper.
A single and Brian Bennett keeps the strike! Slides in a length ball on middle and leg. Brian Bennett tucks it to square leg for a single.
Goes short again and slanting onto the batter, well-directed and Brian Bennett hops and blocks it out.

FOUR! It's either a boundary or a dot right now! Width on offer, slightly shorter and Brian Bennett nicely crunches it through point for a boundary. Brian Bennett is trying to put back the pressure on South Africa.
In two minds! Codi Yusuf sticks to the same length and line, shapes away yet again. Brian Bennett thinks to push but withdraws his bat in the last moment.
BEATEN! Classic stuff from Yusuf! Steams in and lands it outside off on a length, jags away after landing. Brian Bennett without any foot movement tries to push it away but misses.
Codi Yusuf bowls with a width outside off. Brian Bennett has nothing to do with it.
Well bowled! Much better line! Bowls it into the surface, shorter and around off, nips back in. Nick Welch shoulders arms to it.

FOUR! Nick Welch is off the mark with a wonderful shot! Kwena Maphaka mixes his length but pushes it too full and offers a lot of width. Nick Welch leans and creams it square on the off side for a boundary.
Kwena Maphaka goes a touch fuller and targets the pads. Nick Welch keeps it out on the leg side.
On a nagging length and around off. Brian Bennett hangs back, taps it past cover and rotates the strike.
Spills it full and angling down the leg side. Brian Bennett looks to flick but misses it.
FOUR! Second boundary for Brian Bennett! Overpitched by Kwena Maphaka to start his spell, this is outside off. Brian Bennett leans and drives it through covers for a boundary.
Codi Yusuf bowls it on a hard length, outside off, bit of extra bounce. Nick Welch looks to punch it away but misses it. Superb start by Codi Yusuf and South Africa.

OUT! GONE! Maiden wicket for Codi Yusuf as he strikes in the very first over of his Test career. What a special moment for him. Creates an angle as he serves it full and on middle and leg. Takudzwanashe Kaitano plants his front foot across to flick it past square leg but plays it aerially to Tony de Zorzi who takes it low in front of him. Bright start for the young Codi Yusuf. Takudzwanashe Kaitano departs on a golden duck and Zimbabwe are 5/1, trailing by 413 runs.
Takudzwanashe Kaitano c Td Zorzi b C Yusuf 0 (1b 0x4 0x6)
Short of a length and on middle, Brian Bennett gets on his toes and nudges it to square  leg for a single.
Good length delivery, outside off. Brian Bennett shoulders arms to it.

FOUR! Zimbabwe are underway! This is very full and outside off, pitched up and comes with an angle. Brian Bennett drives it square on the off side and it races to the fence. Beats the fielder to his left.
BEATEN! Lovely start! Codi Yusuf serves it on a length, around the fifth stump line and swings it away. Brian Bennett has a poke at it but misses. Bit of shape with the new red-cherry.

SIX! That is some way to end the day's play! Another short-pitched delivery, from around the stumps, on off and middle. Kwena Maphaka reads the length early and pulls it aerially over deep square leg for a six. That was hit with proper timing as well. An action-packed last over, and that will be STUMPS ON DAY 1!

Short and wide of off, Kwena Maphaka skips down the track and frees his arms. Hits it hard through the covers and Wellington Masakadza chases it from the inner ring with a slide. Flicks the ball before the ropes and the replay confirms the same. Two taken.

100 FOR CORBIN BOSCH! His first century in Test cricket! An inning of substance and impact from him! The men in the South African dressing room rise in admiration of his knock! A bouncer from Tanaka Chivanga, on the bodyline, nipping in with some bounce. Corbin Bosch stands tall and pulls this away to deep square leg for a single. Bosch roars out of excitment and rushes to the other hand, gets his helmet off, and raises his bat to the heavens. What a special knock from Bosch this!

DROPPED! That could have been the curtains on South African innings right there, but it has been that kind of a day for the Zimbabweans in the field today! A well-directed short ball, jagging back off the surface, with some extra bounce on it. Corbin Bosch is cramped up for space and tries to pull. Gets the ball high on the body and goes behind off the gloves. The keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga, leaps to his left with his hands overhead, gets his gloves on the ball, but it just deflects off his gloves and lobs behind him. Two taken. That should have been taken! Corbin Bosch moves to 99!
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, just outside off. Corbin Bosch shapes up to pull that away and misses to lay any bat on it.
Good length and outside off. Bosch punches to the cover region.
Kwena Maphaka survives the last ball to bring back Bosch on strike. Overpitched on off, kept out by Maphaka into the leg side.

An appeal for LBW, but not entertained. Just doing a bit much to go down leg. Full and angling on the leg stump line. Kwena Maphaka attempts to work that across but plays over it and is rapped on the front pad.
Slants on the leg stump line, Kwena Maphaka offers no shot and is hit on the front pad. The ball rolls behind to the right of the keeper who stops it.

FOUR LEG BYES! More runs! Sprayed onto the pads, full in length, Kwena Maphaka misses to flick and the ball grazes the front pad. Goes to the right of the keeper and races away to the deep fine leg fence.

Angling into the bodyline, on a length. Kwena Maphaka has no space to work with and to sway away, and takes a blow near the ribs. Corbin Bosch runs to his partner to check and Kwena Maphaka is alright.
Short and going down leg, Kwena Maphaka lets through.

FOUR! Drilled away! The 400 is up for South Africa and Corbin Bosch moves to 97! Pitched a bit too full and on middle and leg, Corbin Bosch shovels the ball and heaves it up and over of mid on for a boundary.
Wide of off, on a length, Corbin Bosch throws his bat at it, to cut, only to miss on the outside edge.
Pace off, short and outside off. Bosch swings to pull but connects thin air.
Full and angling on the leg stump. Bosch steers it towards short fine leg.
Angled down the leg stump line, on a length. Corbin Bosch swivels to pull but misses. The keeper collects and makes a muted appeal for caught behind but gets no support from others in the field.
Fuller and outside on off. Maphaka weighs on the back foot and punches through covers for a single.
Too full and outside off. Bosch lets it be.

FOUR! A schoolboy error there! Shortish length, just outside off. Bosch drags it from outside off and pulls it by rolling his wrists. The ball rolls along the turf to long on and Tanaka Chivanga just doesn't bend low enough to pick the ball up. It passes through the 'London Bridge' and trickles into the fence.
Good length and on the off stump line. Bosch works it away towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Short and outside off, cut away off the back foot to deep point, but Bosch denies the single.

Just in! Short of a length, around the fourth stump line. Corbin Bosch looks to cut but gets more off the outside edge and the ball goes through the backward point region. The man from deep third chases it to his right with a slide and the batters scamper back for the second. Bosch has to hurry to get back to the batting end, however, the throw comes in wide of the keeper who flicks the ball into the stumps. The replay confirms that Bosch just about slid his bat inside the crease before the ball crashed into the stumps.
Nagging length, outside off, cut square to backward point.
Around off, full, pushed with a straight bat off the front foot.

Not Out! Darted fuller and flatter, outside off. Kwena Maphaka prods forward to drive to the cover region, but misses and the keeper collects the ball and dislodges the bails off. Now, the third umpire is brought in to check whether Maphaka's back leg was in the air while the stumps are broken. After a couple of side-on replays, it is confirmed that Maphaka just about plonks his back leg inside the crease, before the keeper flashes off the bails.
Full, flat and on off, Kwena Maphaka blocks it forward.
Overpitched, on middle, Corbin Bosch clips this through square leg and completes the single. Blessing Muzarabani is strolling towards the ball from the deep, but Bosch says no to the second run.
Flat and short, on off, Corbin cuts it to deep cover and refuses the single.
Full and on leg, Bosch flicks it to the left of deep mid-wicket but turns down the single.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! CAUGHT! Blessing Muzarabani's short ball ploy finally gives him his second wicket. He keeps hitting that short of a good length, just around off. It lands and nips back into the batter with some extra lift. Codi Yusuf leans back and plays the uppercut, but picks the man at deep third. Sean Williams runs in a few yards forward and completes the catch. Quite a handy knock from the South African number 10, as Codi Yusuf departs for 27 (49). The visitors are 9 down on 387.
Codi Yusuf c S Williams b B Muzarabani 27 (49b 5x4 0x6)
BEATEN! That in-between length, outside off. Codi Yusuf prepares to play the cut shot, but is beaten by the bounce and it goes past the outside edge.
Short of a length, on off, dabbed to the gully region.

FOUR! Frustrating for Craig Ervine! The deep third was just moved to the deep backward point region and the ball goes to that vacant area. Short, on off, Codi Yusuf is late to cut and it goes off the outside edge and over the slips for a boundary at deep third.
FOUR! Put away! Quick hands from Codi Yusuf! Back of a length, just outside off, Codi Yusuf picks the length in a trice and cuts it over backward point for a cracking boundary.
Short and straight, on off, Corbin Bosch stands tall and pulls it to deep square leg for an easy single.
Lands it fuller and just around off. Codi Yusuf shovels it out to the right of the diving cover fielder.
Full, on the stumps, carved out straight back to the bowler.
Nice and full, floated around off, Codi Yusuf taps it on the bounce to silly mid off.
Full again, turning in off the deck, Corbin Bosch gets low and sweeps it to deep square leg for a single. This brings up the 50-run partnership between Codi Yusuf and Corbin Bosch.
Dropped fuller and in front of the stumps, Corbin Bosch plants his front leg out and flicks this wide of long on to his right for a couple of runs.
Short and on top of off, Corbin hangs back and cuts it straight to point.
An attempted yorker, on middle, flicked straight to mid-wicket by Codi.
Short of a length, nipping back in on top of middle. Codi Yusuf looks to arch back and cut it away, but misses.
FOUR! This is good batting! A nip-backer from outside off, on a short length. Codi Yusuf arches back and just ramps it over the slip cordon for a boundary at deep third.
Oh, some extra lift there! Hard length, outside off, Codi Yusuf leans back to play the square cut on the off side, but gets beaten due to that extra bounce as the ball passes over his angled bat.

Fired on the back of a length, angling on the pads. Codi Yusuf gets inside the line of the ball to nudge it away, but misses and is rapped on the thigh pad. The ball lobs and drops on the pitch to his right.
Back of a length, outside off. Codi Yusuf shapes to pull, but is a bit late on the shot and gets it off the bottom edge of the bat. The ball rolls near the strip on the leg side.
Drifts in on middle and off, Corbin Bosch pushes this full ball to short cover.
Tossed up, full and outside off, Codi Yusuf strides forward and works this in the cover-point gap for a single. The partnership now grows to 43 runs.
Full and around off, eased into the off side.

EDGED, FOUR! More runs for Yusuf and the Proteas. Pitched fuller and on off, Codi Yusuf leans to block it out, but gets a thick outside edge and the ball races away past the right of the first slip. The quick outfield takes the ball into the ropes at deep third.
Short and just outside off. Some bounce on it as it turns away. Corbin Bosch cuts it more off the outside edge as the ball rolls into the short third region. A single taken.
Full, on middle and leg, pushed to the right of the bowler.
Swing and a miss! Blessing Muzarabani pitches this up, full and wide of off, and now gets an away shape. Codi Yusuf slashes at it but misses as the ball curves away.

FOUR! That's been punished by the South African number 10! Too short and really wide of off, Codi Yusuf rises with the bounce and slaps it over the cover fielder for a boundary. Probably not the ideal length with the new ball.
Nagging length, nipping away and bouncing a bit as well. Codi Yusuf lets it be.
Length, on top of off, Codi Yusuf hops on the back foot and drops it with soft hands in front of backward point.
Back of a length, on off, tapped off the back foot to cover.

Bounce right away! Short of a length, on top off, climbing further up. Codi Yusuf is flummoxed with that extra lift and with a fraction of time to get away from the line, the ball hits the handle of the bat.
Short and on off, Codi Yusuf hangs back and punches it to the right of mid off for a single.

In the air...but safe! Tossed up by Vincent Masekesa, on a length, on off, Codi Yusuf clears his front leg to go over mid on. Gets more of a leading edge but manages to evade the back tracking mid off fielder. Two runs taken.
Shorter and outside off, slapped to deep cover for a single.
Floated up, on off, Bosch presses forward and whips it to the right of long on for a brace.
Fuller and on off, Corbin Bosch goes back and pushes it to cover.
FOUR! Thumped! A half-tracker from Vincent Masekesa, on middle and leg, Corbin Bosch backs away and gets his hands through to spank it to the right of mid-wicket for a boundary.
Darted in, on middle and leg, Yusuf gets his bat out in front to stab it down.
Slows it down and drags the length back, on the off stump, Codi keeps it out off the front foot.
Full and on off, firmly driven to cover.
Full and on middle, Codi Yusuf defends it with his bat close to the front pad.
Short and around off, Codi Yusuf pushes it to cover.
Speared in, full and on middle, knocked back to the bowler.

FOUR! Poor delivery and duly punished! A half-tracker, on middle, this stays a bit low but Corbin Bosch does well to stay low and pull it wide of deep square leg for four more. This brings the 350 up for South Africa!
FOUR! Excellent wristwork! Full and attacking the stumps, Corbin Bosch brings his wrists into play and whips it to the right of the man at long on for a boundary.
Full and on middle, Corbin Bosch brings out the broom but gets more of a top edge. It lands it in the vacant deep backward square leg region for a brace.

Edged but safe! On a nagging length, on middle, Codi Yusuf looks to defend it with a straight bat. The ball spins away to catch the outside edge and it goes down on the ground. Races past first slip to his right and the batters run three.
Slower and spinning away, outside off, Yusuf steers it to backward point.
Tossed up, on off, Bosch whips it to long on and crosses over.
Slower and fuller, on off, Yusuf guides it to backward point.
Fired in, full and on the off stump, defended solidly.
Fuller and on middle and leg, jammed out to mid on.
Sliding on with the arm, short and on off, Codi stays back to block.
On off, a bit of extra bounce, Codi Yusuf goes deep in the crease to keep it out.
Short and on off, Corbin cuts it to deep point for a single.
Another googly but this goes down leg, Codi Yusuf lets it go.

Nearly dragged it back onto the stumps! Googly from Vincent Masekesa, too full for the drive, Codi Yusuf goes for it and gets an inside edge onto the pads. It deflects off the pads towards the stumps but luckily for Codi, it trickles just past the off stump.
On a nagging length, on off, Codi taps it to cover.
Looped up, very full, on off, Yusuf eases it back to the bowler.
Fuller and slower, on off, Codi covers the line to block.
Short and on off, Codi dabs it from the crease to backward point.

Three leg byes! Too straight, on the pads, Codi Yusuf misses the tickle. The ball goes off the pads towards deep fine leg. The deep backward square leg fielder runs to his right and cuts it off. Yusuf sprints to complete the third run.
On middle and leg, on a nagging length, played with the turn to deep mid-wicket for one.
Two leg byes! On the pads, on a length, Corbin Bosch reaches out in front for the reverse but fails to get any bat on it. The ball goes off the pads through fine leg for a couple of leg byes.
Pushed through from around the wicket, on middle, Corbin Bosch plays it back to the bowler.
Turning down leg, on a nagging length, Bosch helps it down to deep fine leg for a couple of runs.
Short and on middle, jabbed to short mid-wicket.
Just short! Floated up, on off, Yusuf checks his drive and plays it a bit uppishly. It lands just in front of the diving Vincent Masekesa.
This is the googly from Vincent Masekesa, stays low, short and on middle, Codi Yusuf manages to get behind it.
Drags the length back, outside off, Yusuf presses forward to defend.
Tossed up, full and on off, Codi pushes it back to the bowler.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Vincent Masekesa finally has something to smile about! Looped up, on off, on a length, Keshav Maharaj goes down the track to go back over the bowler's head. Skies it up in front of mid off. Brian Bennett runs across to his right from cover. Keeps his eyes on the ball all the way through and takes a good catch. Keshav Maharaj departs on 21 (30) and South Africa are 330/8 as this 41-run stand comes to an end.
Keshav Maharaj (c) c B Bennett b V Masekesa 21 (30b 1x4 2x6)
Full and on middle, Corbin Bosch backs away and drills it down to long on for one.
Sliding down leg, on a length, Keshav Maharaj misses out on the tickle.
Short and on off, Keshav Maharaj punches it to cover.
This stays low, short and on around leg, Maharaj swipes it to square leg.
Around the pads, on the shorter side, Maharaj turns it to square leg.
SIX! All the way! Wessly Madhevere tosses it up, full and on middle, Keshav Maharaj skips down the track and holds his shape to loft it with a straight bat over long on for a six.
Sliding onto the pads, on a nagging length, Bosch flicks it past mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off, Keshav Maharaj lunges to block it out.
Flatter and around off, Keshav goes back to a full delivery but manages to keep it out.
Turning away, on off, on a nagging length, Maharaj punches it to cover.
Floated up, full and on off, Corbin Bosch brings out the sweep and hits it all along the ground to deep square leg for one.
On off, on a nagging length, Bosch knocks it to cover.
Very full, on middle, jammed out back to the bowler by Bosch.

FOUR! Uppish but in the gap! This is on a short of a length, outside off, Keshav Maharaj jabs at the ball with hard hands. Gets it off the outer half and it goes uppishly but between gully and backward point for a four.
Around leg, on a back of a length, Corbin nudges it behind square on the leg side for one.
On a hard length, on middle, Corbin Bosch stands tall and pulls it to the right of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Fuller and on off, patted down the deck by Bosch.

FOUR! Flayed away and that will be FIFTY for Corbin Bosch! An impressive knock so far from Bosch. On a back of a length, wide on off, Bosch throws his hands at the ball and gets a thickish outside edge that flies over the slip cordon.
Angling in, on off, on a length, Bosch pushes it to mid off.
Shorter and on off, Keshav pushes it to cover.
Full and on middle, eased back to the bowler.

SIX! First six for Keshav Maharaj in this test! Vincent Masekesa serves it on the fuller and on the middle and leg. Keshav Maharaj puts the dancing shoes on and gets to the pitch of the ball to hammer it down the ground over long off for a biggie.
Slower and fuller, on the off stump. Turning away from the batter and Keshav Maharaj watchfully leaves it alone.
Tossed up, on off. Keshav Maharaj drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller, and on the stumps. Keshav Maharaj taps it to cover.
Short, outside off. Corbin Bosch lets it be.
On the back of a length, outside off. Corbin Bosch clips it to the mid-wicket region for a brace.
Short of a length, outside off. Corbin Bosch looks to cut but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller, on the stumps. Corbin Bosch blocks it back.
On a length, angling onto the pads. Keshav Maharaj looks to flick but misses it and gets hit on the front pad. The ball rolled towards mid-wicket for a leg bye.
Bowls it on the good length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj punches it to cover.
Shortish and outside off. Keshav Maharaj cuts it to point for a single.
Fuller and on the pads. Keshav Maharaj drives it to mid on.
300 up for South Africa! Fuller and slower, on the stumps. Corbin Bosch clips it to mid on for one.
Shortish, on the middle. Corbin Bosch makes some room and taps it back to the bowler.
Short and around off, Bosch cuts it to the left of deep cover for a couple.
Short and on off, pushed to cover by Bosch.
Shorter, outside off. Keshav Maharaj lets it be.
On a back of a length, around off, Keshav guides it to backward point.

In the air but lands safe! Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on a short length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj goes for the pull but gets a top edge towards the deep backward square leg region. Sean Williams does well running to his left to keep it to two.
Short length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj ducks underneath it.
Drags the length back, on the stumps. Keshav Maharaj blocks it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj plays inside the line and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Fuller and on the off stump. Keshav Maharaj skips down the track and drives it aerially to the left of mid off for one.
Slower and fuller, outside off. Corbin Bosch cuts it to deep point for one.
Darted in, full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
Tossed up, on off, driven to cover.

Bit of a yes and no between the batters! Wellington Masakadza bowls it on a fuller length and on the stumps. Corbin Bosch flicks it to mid-wicket and the mid on fielder gives it a long chase. Corbin Bosch wants the third run but is sent back by Keshav. Two runs taken.
Fuller and on the stumps. Corbin Bosch clips it to mid-wicket.
On a nagging length, outside off, left alone by Keshav.
On a length, on the off stump. Keshav Maharaj defends it to the off side.
Short and outside off. Corbin Bosch rides the bounce and works it to square leg for one.
Back of a length, outside off. Keshav Maharaj rocks back and taps it to mid-wicket for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! End of a magnificent knock on debut from the debutant Lhuan-dre Pretorius! The only loose shot he has played, seemingly. On the other hand, Tanaka Chivanga continues to ace with the ball as he gets his fourth wicket. Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on a short length and outside off from around the wicket. Lhuan-dre Pretorius goes for the pull shot but gets the top edge because of the steep bounce. The ball flies towards the mid on region where Wellington Masakadza takes a regulation catch. Lhuan-dre Pretorius departs for 153 (160), and South Africa are seven down.
Lhuan-dre Pretorius c W Masakadza b T Chivanga 153 (160b 11x4 4x6)
Starts from around the wicket and bowls it on short length, outside off. Corbin Bosch rides the bounce and taps it to deep point for one.
Shorter and on off, Bosch goes back and taps it wide of point for one.

Top edge but safe! Floated up, on off, Corbin Bosch reaches out in front for the sweep. Gets a top edge but it lands in the vacant fine leg region. The deep backward square leg fielder mops it up to his right. Two runs taken.
On the pads, on a length, turned away past mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on off, pushed to cover.

FOUR! Simply superb and that brings up 150 for Lhuan-dre Pretorius! The young southpaw continues on his merry way. Floated up, full and wide on off, Pretorius gets on the front foot and drives it to the right of the diving cover fielder for a boundary. This also brings up the 100-run partnership between Pretorius and Bosch.
Short and on off, cut away to deep point for a single.

FOUR! Lhuan-dre Pretorius is on the charge and smashed the third boundary of the over! Tanaka Chivanga pitches it on the back of a length, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius from the back foot punches to the left of mid on for a boundary.

FOUR! The second of the over! Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on short length, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius brings his wrists into play as he gets on the back foot and pulls it along the ground to deep fine leg for a boundary.
Down the leg side, on a length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius lets it be.
Outside off, left alone by Lhuan-dre Pretorius.

FOUR! Glorious drive by Lhuan-dre Pretorius! Tanaka Chivanga serves it on the fuller length and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius comes forward and plays with the straight bat to drive it down the ground. The ball races away ​​​​​​past mid on to his left for a boundary.
On a length, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius rides the bounce and cuts it nicely to the right of the deep backward point for a brace.
Full and on off, blocked out.

FOUR! Straight down the ground! Wellington Masakadza serves it on the fuller and on the stumps. Corbin Bosch gets on the front foot and gets to the pitch of the ball to drive it down the ground. The fielder at mid on dives but is unable to stop it from racing away for a boundary.

An appeal of LBW but the umpire stays unmoved. Wellington Masakadza bowls it fuller and on the leg stump. Corbin Bosch looks to flick but misses it and wears on the pad. Looked to be sliding down the leg side.
Short, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius works it across to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Shortish, on middle and off. Bosch rocks back and works it to cover for a single.
Full, on the pads. Corbin Bosch blocks it to short mid wicket.
Fuller and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets on the front foot and drives it to extra cover.
On a nagging length, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius works it to mid on.
Shortish and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius cuts it wide of deep backward point for a couple of runs.
Bowls it on the back of a length, slanting down the leg side. Lhuan-dre Pretorius clips it behind square. The fielder at fine leg runs across and keeps it to two.
Nails the yorker on the middle and off. Corbin Bosch gets his bat down in time and squeezes it to mid-wicket for a run.

FOUR! Bosch welcomes Tanaka Chivanga with a four! Tanaka Chivanga serves it on a good length and angling into the batter from over the wicket. Corbin Bosch stays on the back foot and stands tall to punch it nicely to deep backward point for a boundary.
This keeps low, short and flat, on the off stump, Corbin Bosch does well to stay low and chop it past backward point for a run. The 250 is up for South Africa!
Stays around the wicket for the right-hander, darted in, on off, Corbin Bosch pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and on off, Pretorius backs away and knocks it to long off for a single.
Slows it down but keeps the length full, on middle, worked with the turn to short mid-wicket.
Full and attacking the front pad, Pretorius gets his bat out in front to block.
Tossed up from around the wicket, on a length, on leg, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets forward to defend.
At the stumps, on a nagging length, Corbin Bosch gets right behind it to keep it out. That will be TEA on Day 1!
Short and on off, Pretorius goes on the back foot and punches it to long on for a single.
On off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius works it to mid off.
Full and on off, played back to the bowler by Pretorius.

Edged and gone! Or is it? Zimbabwe think so but the finger stays down and they cannot challenge the decision due to the unavailability of DRS. Pushed through, short and on off, Pretorius is a bit late to bring his bat down. The ball sneaks under the bat and the keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga is up in an appeal for caught behind but the umpire shakes his head.
SIX! BANG! Tonked! A half-tracker from around the wicket, around off, there to be put away, Pretorius obliges as he stands tall and muscles the pull over mid-wicket for a biggie.
Bowled with a flatter trajectory, just outside the off stump, Corbin Bosch chops it down off the back foot to backward point.
Coming in with the arm, short and on the off stump, Bosch is watchful as he knocks it to cover.
Slower and fuller, on middle, Pretorius makes room and eases it to long off for one more.
Landing outside the line of the leg stump, flat and short, Lhuan-dre Pretorius pads it away.
Turning into the pads, full and around leg, Pretorius looks to defend it with a straight bat. The ball spins to catch the inside edge and it rolls wide of fine leg for another couple.
Short and down the leg side, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets inside the line and helps it to the left of the man at deep fine leg for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Gets it through! A bit too full, outside off, Corbin Bosch gets on the front foot and drives it to the right of the diving cover fielder for a boundary.
