Short and around leg, Corbin Bosch gets low to pull it straight to square leg.
Full and on middle, Bosch looks to work it with the spin. Gets a soft leading edge in front of cover.
Tossed up, full and on off, Corbin lunges to block.
Short and around leg, Bosch jabs it off the back foot to square leg.
Short and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius drags the pull towards mid-wicket where a half-stop by the diving fielder allows the batters to cross for one.
Slanted in, on the off stump, Corbin goes back and taps it to cover.
Floated up, on off, Pretorius works this full ball to long on for a run. The 50-run stand comes up between these two batters!
Short and wide on off, hit with a horizontal bat to deep cover for a single.
Fuller and slower, going across, Pretorius pushes it to long off and gets to the other end.
On middle and leg, on a nagging length, Pretorius gets forward to defend.
Full and on middle, swept through square leg for a single by Bosch.
Looped up, full and wide on off, Pretorius frees his arms and crunches it to the left of deep point for a brace.
Sliding on with the angle, on the off stump, Pretorius gets his bat out in front to keep it out.
Full and around off, firmly driven but Pretorius can't get it past the man at extra cover.
Low full toss, on off, Corbin drills it down to long on for one more.
Short and on off, cut away to deep point for a single.
Full and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius drives it to short mid off.
Fired in, quicker and on off, Bosch eases it to cover.
Slows it down and gets the ball to spin away, short and on off, Corbin presses back to cut it to cover.
Fuller and on off, Corbin defends it off the front foot.
Darted into the right-hander, on off, Bosch taps it to cover.
Sliding on again, flat and short, on off, Bosch punches it to a straightish short cover.
Short and coming on with the arm, on off, Corbin Bosch pushes it from the crease to cover.
Full and attacking the stumps, reverse swept to deep backward point for a run.
Short and on off, Pretorius punches it down to long on and takes one.
Pushed through, well outside off, Pretorius lets it be.
Fuller and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius plays it back to the bowler.
Sprayed on the pads, Bosch goes back and helps it down to deep fine leg for one.
Spinning back in, around off, Corbin lunges to defend.
Hangs it up there, on middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets forward to smother the spin.
Offers flight, full and on middle and leg, Corbin Bosch sweeps it firmly to deep backward square leg for a single.
Back to bowling it fuller and slower, on off, knocked back to the bowler.
Keeps it short, on middle, Corbin Bosch backs away and slaps it to extra cover.
Slightly shorter, on the off stump, Bosch punches it to cover.
Drifting in, full and on middle, Corbin blocks it out.
Sliding on with the arm, on the pads, on a length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius tucks it to mid-wicket.

SIX! Effortless! Brian Bennett gives the ball air from around the wicket, on a length, on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius presses forward and just extends his hands into the lofted stroke. Clears the leaping long off fielder for a six.
Slower and shorter, on middle, Corbin goes deep in the crease and pulls it to deep square leg for one more.
Tossed up, full and on middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius pushes it to long off and crosses over.
Short and turning in, on middle, Bosch presses back and punches it to long on for one.
Short and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius goes back and flat bats it down to long on for a single.
Full and on off, Corbin Bosch defends it off the front foot.
Floated up, eased down to long on for a single by Lhuan-dre Pretorius.
Darted across, on a length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius mistimes the drive to cover.
Full and around leg, Lhuan-dre Pretorius nudges it to mid-wicket.
Short and flat, on off, punched past backward point for a single.

HUNDRED FOR PRETORIUS ON TEST DEBUT! Stuff of dreams for the young left-hander. Not just the situation he walked in but the way he has looked at ease so far has been really impressive. Full and on the pads, Lhuan-dre Pretorius brings his wrists into play and works it through square leg for a single to bring up his maiden Test hundred. His teammates are all up on the balcony to applaud his knock.
The debutant moves to 99! Full, flat and quick, on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius with a gentle push down to long off for a single.
Full and on off, pushed to the off side.
Full and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius plans his foot forward and pushes it to short cover.

FOUR! Just goes all the way! Lhuan-dre Pretorius moves to 98! Brian Bennett gives the ball more air, and lands it outside leg, on a fullish length. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets forward with a big stride and steers it very fine to deep fine leg. It slows down on its way to the ropes, but by the time deep backward square leg fielder intercepts it with a despairing dive, it trickles into the ropes.
Pulls the length back, does Brian, on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius stands tall and punches this to mid on.
Pushed through full and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius leans forward to defend, but it goes off the leading edge to the point region.
Good delivery! This is that in-drifter, full and sliding on middle and leg. Corbin Bosch presses ahead to block but gets an inside edge onto the front pad.
Looped fuller and on off, drilled down to long off for a single.
Short of off, quicker on off, Corbin Bosch quickly goes back inside the crease and cuts it square to deep point for a single. 200 IS UP FOR SOUTH AFRICA!
Tossed up through the air, full and across off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius with a huge lunge forward, pushes it wide of mid off for a quick single.
Dragged length, on the leg stump line. Lhuan-dre Pretorius nudges it to backward square leg.
Floated full and on leg, clipped to short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Shouts of 'catch it', but it misses everyone and races away! Short ball, spinning on the leg stump, Corbin Bosch is quick to go back and across and pulls it over square leg and to the left of the deep mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Touch full and drifting on middle and leg. Knocked back to the bowler.
Goes straight on with the arm, on a length, on top of off. Corbin Bosch goes back and across to cut but misses as the ball passes above his angled bat.
Landed fuller, outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius steers it away to backward point for a single.
Nice and full, on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius leans on and eases into the off side.
Shortish delivery, on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius hangs back and punches it across to the leg side.
Too full, drifting across the batter from around the stumps. Lhuan-dre Pretorius prods forward and drives it down to long off for a single.
Drags the length back, on off, Corbin Bosch hangs back and punches it through cover-point for a single.
Arm ball, full and on the stumps, defended straight back.
Flights it on middle, Corbin Bosch keeps this full ball out.
Floated up, full and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius skips forward and pushes it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Full, on off, pushed to cover.
Turns sharply into the batter, fuller in length, Corbin Bosch tries the reverse sweep but misses.
Spins in from off, full in length, Corbin Bosch hangs back and taps it on the pitch.
Full and on off, driven to short cover.
Pushed through, full and on middle, Corbin Bosch drives it back to the bowler.
Dropped short and outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius hangs back and cuts it to deep point for a single.
Nice and full, on off, eased into the off side.
Full and pitched just outside leg. Bosch clips it to short mid-wicket.
Flighted fuller and across off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius pushes it wide of cover for a single.
Dropped fuller and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius leans on and eases it to short cover.
Tossed up, full on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets forward and defends to the off side with a straight bat.
Sprayed down leg, on a length. Lhuan-dre Pretorius shapes to pull but aborts and leaves.
Full and on off, pushed to the off side.
Short and outside off. Pretorius rocks back and punches it wide of point for one.

DROPPED! Oh, dear! How costly will this prove for the Chevrons? That was a straightforward chance in all fairness! Short and on middle, spinning in, Corbin Bosch hangs back and pulls it flat and straight towards the square leg fielder. Clive Madande in as a substitute at square leg is a bit late to react and is beaten by the pace of the ball, and it bursts through his hands and rolls behind. A single taken.
Full on the middle stump. Bosch works it to the widish short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, smashed through covers for a single.
Short and wide of off. Pretorius cuts it through backward point for a couple of runs.
Sliding on the leg stump, on a length, nudged away to square leg for a single.
Short and just outside off. Bosch hangs back and cuts it to deep cover for one. Gets off the mark.
This one goes in with the arm, quicker and flatter, drifting on the leg stump. Bosch misses the flick on the inside edge and gets hit on the front pad. A slight appeal for LBW, but dies down.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! Zimbabwe gradually making inroads in the session as Wellington Masakadza gets his first wicket. Nicely floated full, drifting into the middle stump line. It lands and spins away from the batter. Kyle Verreynne plants his leg in front to push it straight, but since the ball spins away across the batter, the outside edge is found. It goes flat and low to the right of the first slip. Craig Ervine bends low and snaffles it easily.
Kyle Verreynne (wk) c C Ervine b W Masakadza 10 (16b 2x4 0x6)
Nice and full, on off, blocked straight back.
FOUR! Good shot! Short of full, outside off, Kyle Verreynne rocks back and cuts it past backward point for a boundary.
Drags the length back, on the leg stump, Lhuan-dre Pretorius hangs back and pins it into the mid-wicket region for a single.
Full and straight on off, Kyle Verreynne presses forward and pushes it to the cover region.

Pitched fuller and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius plays with a straight bat face and drives it wide of mid off. The ball slows down on the way to the deep and is chased by the mid off fielder. Three taken.
Short and outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius controls the pull to square leg.
Back of a length on the pads, Kyle Verreynne gets across the line to flick and the ball goes off the front pad to short fine leg. They cross for a leg bye.
Angling in on middle and leg, Lhuan-dre Pretorius tucks this wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length, on top of off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius opens the bat face late and dabs it beside the strip on the off side.
Flat and short, on middle, Kyle hangs back to block.
Tossed up, on off, played back to the bowler.
Floated up, eased down to long on for a single.
Low full toss, on off, knocked down to long off for one.
Low full toss, on middle, Kyle Verreynne whips it to mid-wicket.
Turning in, full and on middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius lunges to block. Gets an inside edge that rolls behind on the leg side for one.
Angled in at the hips, on a back of a length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius tucks it through mid-wicket for one.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Too straight from Blessing Muzarabani, on a back of a length, around leg, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets inside the line and helps it down to deep fine leg for a boundary.
On a hard length, on middle, tucked beside the strip on the leg side.
Kyle Verreynne once again gets lucky here, as he might have been run out!
On a nagging length, outside off. Kyle Verreynne drives it to the mid off fielder.
Short length, on the middle and off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius rocks back and pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, around off, pushed into the off side.
Flatter and shorter, on off, Kyle rocks back to defend.
Slower and fuller, on the stumps. Kyle Verreynne taps it to short mid-wicket.

FOUR! Edged away! Vincent Masekesa bowls it on a fuller and outside off. It turns away from the batter, and Kyle Verreynne looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. It goes past the outstretched right hand of the first slip fielder for a boundary to the third man region.
Pushed through, short and on off, punched past point for one.

SIX! Lhuan-dre Pretorius continues his attacking approach! Vincent Masekesa serves it on a fuller length and outside the off stump from over the wicket. Lhuan-dre Pretorius dances down the track and gets to the pitch of the ball to smash it over long off for a biggie.
On a back of a length, on off, Kyle Verreynne gets behind it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Zimbabwe gets a crucial breakthrough as the partnership was growing brilliantly between these two batters. Blessing Muzarabani bends his back and pitches it on the short of a length, wide outside the off stump. Dewald Brevis gets deep in his crease and looks to pull that one, but gets the toe end of the bat. The ball flies toward mid off, where Tanaka Chivanga dives forward to take a good catch. Dewald Brevis departs for 51 (41), and South Africa are 150/5.
Dewald Brevis c T Chivanga b B Muzarabani 51 (41b 3x4 4x6)
Full length, on the off stump. Dewald Brevis gets on the front foot and works it to point.
Fuller, and on the middle and leg. Dewald Brevis drills it to mid on.
Shorter, angling down the leg side. Lhuan-dre Pretorius looks to clip it, but gets a glove on to that one to the left of the keeper for a single. The 150 is up for South Africa!
From around the wicket and on a good length, on the off stump. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets on the back foot and blocks it.

SIX! FIFTY FOR BREVIS ON DEBUT IN 38 BALLS! Dewald has announced his arrival in style. Loopy delivery, lowish full toss, on middle, Brevis takes it on the full and stays low to swat it over mid-wicket for a flat six. Third six of the over and Vincent Masekesa continues to leak runs.

SIX! Another biggie of the over and this time down the ground! Vincent Masekesa bowls it fuller and outside off. Dewald Brevis is not missing out on that one as he sits down on one knee and smashes it over long-off for another biggie.
Shorter and on the stumps, Dewald Brevis works it to short mid-wicket..
SIX! Up and away! Vincent Masekesa serves it on the shorter length, outside the leg stump. Dewald Brevis rocks back on the back foot and pulls it over deep backward square leg for a biggie.
Tossed up and fuller. Lhuan-dre Pretorius skips down the track and hits it to long on for one.
Fuller and off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius defends it back to the bowler.
On the back of the length, angling into the batter. Dewald Brevis rocks back and looks to clip it, but misses it.
On a good length, wide outside off. Dewald Brevis shoulders arms at it.
Touch fuller and outside off. Dewald Brevis gets on the front foot and drives it to the mid off fielder.
Full length, on off and middle. Dewald Brevis gets behind the line and blocks it to mid on.
On a good length and outside off. Dewald Brevis defends it to the off side.
Comes from around the wicket and bowls it on a length, on the off stump. Lhuan-dre Pretorius clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
On the pads, flicked past mid-wicket for one by Lhuan-dre Pretorius.
More flight on this one, on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius squeezes it out to the off side.
Looped up, full, on middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius steps down the track and carves it to short cover.
On off, on a nagging length, on off, Dewald Brevis pushes it wide of cover for one.
Tossed up and fuller, on the stumps. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets on the front foot and drives it to long on for one.
Fuller, on off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius taps it to the cover region.
Back of a length, just around off, Dewald Brevis gets on top of the ball and knocks it straight to mid off.
On a back of a length, on off, jabbed through square leg for one.
Shortish and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius rocks back for the pull but gets a top edge which flies over the slip cordon. Two runs taken.

Had to hurry! Good length, on top of off, Dewald Brevis gets inside the line and tucks it in front of mid on and sets off for a single. The mid on fielder is a bit closer and hence Brevis had to put on his skates. Dives to get to the other end as the fielder misses to score a direct hit.
On a hard length, on off, stabbed down on the off side by Brevis.
Comes from over the wicket and bowls it on a good length and on the leg stump. Dewald Brevis works it to mid on.
Floated up, full and on off, Brevis smacks it along the ground to long off for one.
Flatter and quicker, on the stumps. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets  on the back foot and works it to mid-wicekt for a single.

A huge appeal of LBW, but the umpire is unmoved. Vincent Masekesa pitches it on a fuller and on the stumps. Lhuan-dre Pretorius sits down on one knee for the reverse sweep but misses it and wears it on the thigh pad. That looked straight and Pretorius seems to have gotten away with another one here.
Fuller and slower outside off. Dewald Brevis rocks back and cuts it to the deep point for one.
Fuller and outside off. Dewald Brevis gets on the front foot and drives it to cover.

Good work in the deep! Vincent Masekesa bowls it from over the wicket, fuller and just outside off stump. Lhuan-dre Pretorius drives it through covers, and the fielder at the sweeper cover runs to his left and save a run for his side. Three runs taken.
Drops it on the short length. Brevis ducks underneath it.

FOUR! Easy pickings for Dewald Brevis! Tanaka Chivanga serves this one on a short length, outside off from over the wicket. Dewald Brevis stands tall, and the ball sits up nicely for him to pull in front of square over the mid-wicket for a boundary.
On a length, angling into the batter. Lhuan-dre Pretorius tucks it to the right of the deep square leg for a single.
Bowls around the sixth stump line, on a good length. Lhuan-dre Pretorius shoulders arms at it.
On the back of a length, wide outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius leaves it alone to the keeper.
Starts from around the wicket, pitches it on the short of a length, wide outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius lets it go.

FOUR! Poor and rightly punished! A low full toss, on the stumps, Brevis gets low, spreads over the crease, and drills it down the ground for a boundary. A very expensive over from Vincent Masekesa as 13 runs come off it. This has been a really positive start to the post-Lunch session for South Africa.

SIX! BANG! Short and turns into the batter, there to be hit. Dewald Brevis hangs back and swings with the spin. Pulls it aerially, and parks it behind deep mid-wicket for half a dozen. The ball has scuffed up and it is being changed. This also brings up the 50-run partnership between these two.

FIFTY ON DEBUT FOR LHUAN-DRE PRETORIUS! And it has come off just 53 deliveries. He has come out with intent and has produced a good knock for his side so far. Full and on the stumps, pushed with a flick to widish mid-wicket for a single. A calm celebration from the debutant as he gets to the other end, raises his bat and soaks in the applause from his teammates.
Lhuan-dre Pretorius defends this ball straight back.
The 100 is up for South Africa! Uppish for a moment, but safe enough. Full and outside off, Dewald Brevis slices it over mid off and the ball dribbles towards long off. One taken.
Full and flat, on the leg stump, Lhuan-dre Pretorius sweeps this to deep fine leg for a single.
Good length, outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius prods foward and taps this between cover and point for a quick single.
Hard length, on middle, Brevis tucks this across to the right of mid on for a single.
BEATEN! Length, outside off, nibbling away. Dewald Brevis with a tentative push on the front foot is beaten on the outside edge.

Good work in the deep there! Back of a length, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius frees his arms and cuts it behind square on the off side. The ball rolls towards the deep backward point fence and is chased with a slide from the fielder who sprints to his right from deep cover. Three taken.
Short of a length, on off, Dewald Brevis mistimes his pull shot and gets off the toe end of the bat. A single wide of mid-wicket.

Starts with a full ball, on middle, Dewald Brevis plays with a straight bat and pushes it down the ground. Blessing Muzarabani from mid on chases it down in the deep and the batters hare back for the second.

FOUR! Pulled away! Short ball, spinning back in from middle. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets the ball at a good height as he swivels and pulls it along the ground to the leg side. The fielder from deep square leg sprints after it to his right, but the ball beats his chase and races into the fence. And that will be LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Full and floated on middle, pushed back at the bowler.
FOUR! Nice shot! Drops it a bit too short, does Vincent Masekesa, around off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets enough width on that one and cuts it powerfully to the deep point region for a boundary.
Full and on the stumps, spinning in. Lhuan-dre Pretorius blocks it off the inside half of the bat as the ball rolls into the leg side.
An in-drifter, full and on middle. Dewald Brevis plants his front foot ahead and carves it through cover for a single.
Pushed through, full and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius drives it to the mid off region for a single.
FOUR! Classic! A fraction full and outside off, Dewald Brevis strides across and caresses this through extra cover for a boundary.
Nipping away from outside off, Brevis leaves this length ball.
Fuller and on middle and leg, Lhuan-dre Pretorius drives it straight down the ground, but the ball slows down before the ropes and is chased down by the mid on fielder. Three taken.

On a good length, pitching outside off and cutting back in sharply. Lhuan-dre Pretorius leans forward to block but gets a thick inside edge onto the front pad as the ball rolls on the pitch. And another No Ball as Tanaka Chivanga has overstepped!
Back of a length, angling in on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius hangs back and knocks it onto the surface.
Short and climbing over the batter. Lhuan-dre Pretorius sits down to dodge this.
Nagging length, outside off, left alone.
Length, on middle, tucked across to mid-wicket.
Spins in from middle, on a fuller length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius steers it behind square on the leg side for a single at deep fine leg.
Short and on off, spinning away. Dewald Brevis rocks back and cuts it to deep extra cover for a single.
Full and on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and on the leg stump line. Lhuan-dre Pretorius pulls this off the inside half of the bat to deep fine leg for a single.
Full, on off, driven wide of mid off for a single.

Almost a celebrappeal for caught behind, but the umpire is unmoved. The bowler and the players behind the wickets look very certain that they have got their man, but since there's no review system available, Lhuan-dre Pretorius stays. This is full and just outside off. Lands and nips back into the left hander. Lhuan-dre Pretorius is a bit late to plant his front foot out and by the time his bat comes down, the ball sneaks in. He plays over the line and the ball passes close to the inside edge on the way to the keeper. The Chevrons believe that there was an edge, but with no reviews in this series, it ends in disappointment for the hosts.
Full and around off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius leans on the front foot and pushes this straight to the cover fielder.

FOUR! A southpaw's delight! Digs it in short and outside off. It lands and lifts off the deck. Lhuan-dre Pretorius waits for it and rises with the bounce to cut it behind square on the off side for a boundary at deep backward point.
Hard length, fairly outside off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius shoulders arms.
Outside off, on the good length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius pushes hard at it, but with barely any foot movement. Gets an inside edge of the bat as the ball rolls to the left of the bowler.
Length ball, wide of off, left alone by Lhuan-dre Pretorius. A late call for No Ball from the umpire as Tanaka Chivanga has overstepped.
Short, nipping back into the batter from off. Dewald Brevis swivels and pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Length, around off and middle, Dewald Brevis works this across, from the inner half of the bat, to the mid on region for a single.

Full in length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius clips this along the ground to the mid-wicket region. The fielder from the deep runs forward but does not quite bend enough to pick the ball and it rolls behind. A single taken.
Full and on middle and off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius pushes it down to the ground, to the left of mid off for a couple of runs.

Just holds a bit in the surface, on top of off, turning away. Dewald Brevis stands tall to cut it away, but gets a thick inside edge. The ball then dribbles over the stumps and rolls to the backward square leg region. A single taken.
Too full, drifting into the stumps. Dewald Brevis gets lured in the flight but mistimes his heave and hits it off the toe end of the bat. The ball drops just short of the mid on fielder.
Lhuan-dre Pretorius clips this ball through mid-wicket for a single.
Proper bouncer, on the bodyline. Dewald Brevis ducks under it.
On the good length, jagging back in. Pretorius misses the flick on the inside edge. Gets rapped on the front thigh pad as the ball rolls into the leg side. A leg bye taken.
On a length and around the off stump. Pretorius blocks it down.

OUT! RUN OUT! Dear o dear! A massive, massive mix-up in between and South Africa lose their fourth wicket. And just as the partnership for this fourth wicket was blooming nicely, this wicket has come at a perfect time for the hosts. This is on a good length, nipping into the right hander. Wiaan Mulder hops on the back foot and stabs it to the right of the pitch and sniffs a single. Lhuan-dre Pretorius is keen to cross over, but Wiaan Mulder takes a couple of steps ahead and reluctantly slows down, but decides to cross over. Blessing Muzarabani runs across the batters to collect the ball, which further slows down the momentum of Wiaan. Blessing Muzarabani picks the ball and quickly turns around, releases the throw, flat and scores a direct hit at the bowler's end. Wiaan Mulder jogs off to reach but is well short.
Wiaan Mulder run out (Blessing Muzarabani) 17 (47b 1x4 0x6)
Length-delivery, on off, Wiaan Mulder rises with the bounce and drops it on the pitch.

Uh, oh! No Ball for overstepping! Dug in well short by Blessing Muzarabani, on the leg stump line, and climbing over the shoulders. Lhuan-dre Pretorius swivels and pulls it to deep fine leg. The fielder there is a bit square and has to run across to the left to mop it up. One taken.
Nagging length, on off, knocked out to the off side.

FOUR! Lovely shot! The 50 comes up for South Africa! Drops a half volley, does Masakadza, right in front of the sticks. Wiaan Mulder shimmies down the track and smashes it gun-barrel straight down the ground for a cracking boundary. The partnership moves to 30 between these two.
Slower and outside the leg stump, Lhuan-dre Pretorius plays it with the turn and pushes it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Too full, on the stumps, drilled down straight to mid on for a quick single.
Flighted nicely through the air, full and on middle. Wiaan Mulder gets it off the leading edge to the point region.
Some turn from that fuller length, on off. Wiaan Mulder presses forward and eases it out to the off side.
Nice and full, on middle, Wiaan Mulder leans on it and defends it straight.
Touch full and on off, tapped out by Lhuan-dre Pretorius to the cover region.

It's heating up a bit now! A well-directed short ball, angling into the bodyline, with some lift on it. Lhuan-dre Pretorius goes for the pull shot, but misses. The keeper collects it over his head and Blessing Muzarabani gives a bit of an earful to the batter.

Edged, but well short! Around the wickets, back of a length, angling in and with some extra bit of bounce. Lhuan-dre Pretorius brings his bat in front to deal with it. As he goes with soft hands, the ball does catch the outside edge, but drops well ahead of the gully fielder.
That uneven bounce again! Short in length, cutting back in a touch, and staying a tad low on the bounce. Wiaan Mulder manages to control the pull shot to deep fine leg for a single.
Outside off, on a hard length, Wiaan Mulder lets the ball arrive and taps it with soft hands to the point region.
Hits the deck hard, does Blessing, angling on top of middle. Wiaan Mulder gets right behind the line and bunts it onto the pitch.
Touch fuller and on the off stump. Wiaan Mulder drives it to the cover region. Single taken.
Slower and fuller, outside off. Wiaan Mulder drills it straight to the mid off fielder.
Fuller, on off. Wiaan Mulder lunges forward and blocks it.

Ouch! Takudzwanashe Kaitano has copped a nasty blow at short leg. Short and on leg, Lhuan-dre Pretorius rocks back and crunches the pull. Kaitano, under the helmet at short leg with the shades on is unable to duck under it in time. The ball hits him on the visor of the helmet and rolls behind. A single is taken but Pretorius is quick to check on Kaitano.
Fuller and slower, around the off stump. Lhuan-dre Pretorius looks to defend but gets an outside edge to the first slip. Two runs taken.
From over the wicket, fuller on off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius blocks it off the front foot.
Short and outside off, rising up off the deck. Wiaan Mulder lets it be.
BEATEN! Good length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder looks to block it from the crease and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Bangs it short. Wiaan Mulder ducks underneath it.
On a nagging length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder gets on top of the bounce and taps it towards point.
On a good length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder gets on the back foot and guides it to point.
On a length, just outside off. Wiaan Mulder works it to the cover region.

FOUR! Another crunchy drive from the batter! Wellington Masakadza tosses it up, just around the off stump. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets forward and gets to the pitch of the ball to drive that one through extra cover for a boundary.
Shorter, outside leg. Wiaan Mulder goes on the back foot and punches it wide of the covers for a single.
Fuller, around off. Wiaan Mulder gets on the front foot and blocks it.
Looped up, full and on off, Lhuan-dre Pretorius eases it to long off and crosses over.
Full and on off, knocked back to the bowler by Lhuan-dre Pretorius.
Floated, full and slow, on off, driven to deep cover for one by Mulder.
On a good length, on the leg side. Lhuan-dre Pretorius shoulders arms at it.
On a length, sliding down the leg side. Lhuan-dre Pretorius looks to flick but doesn't get any connection on that.
On middle, on a short of a length, Lhuan-dre Pretorius blocks it out off the back foot.
On a back of a length, on middle, Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets right behind it.

Peach! Blessing Muzarabani bowls this one on a short of a length, outside off. The ball gets an extra bounce off the deck, and Lhuan-dre Pretorius plays inside the line and gets beaten on the outside edge.
From around the wicket and bangs it on the short of a length, on the off-stump. Lhuan-dre Pretorius ducks underneath it.

Floated fuller and just around off. Wiaan Mulder drives this inside out to the left of mid off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius looks to pinch in a single, but is sent back by Mulder as the fielder is quick to get on the ball.
Fuller and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius drives it to the cover region for one.
Shortish, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius rocks back and taps it to the off side.

FOUR! Classical cover drive on that one! Wellington Masakadza keeps it full and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius gets on the front foot and drives it crisply along the ground through covers for a boundary.

SIX! Bangs it down the ground! Wellington Masakadza gives a bit more air on that one and bowls it fuller and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius puts on the dancing shoes and gets to the pitch of the ball to hammer it down the ground over long off for a biggie!
From over the wicket and bowls it fuller and outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius taps it to mid-wicket.
Full length, on middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder blocks it to the leg side.
Comes from over the wicket and bowls it on a hard length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder defends it back to the bowler.
First runs for Lhuan-dre Pretorius in Test cricket! Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on a full length, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius plants his front foot forward and drives it to cover for a single.
On the back of a length, outside off. Lhuan-dre Pretorius leaves it alone to the keeper.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! One brings two Zimbabwe! They are all over the reigning champions at the moment. Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on the back of a length, around outside off stump. The ball gets a good bounce off the pitch, and David Bedingham pokes at it from the crease and gets an outside edge to first slip. Craig Ervine takes a good catch there around his neck. David Bedingham departs on 0 (3) and South Africa are 23/3.
David Bedingham c C Ervine b T Chivanga 0 (3b 0x4 0x6)
Angled in at the hips, on a back of a length, Mulder tucks it wide of square leg for a single.
Fuller and slower, on off, David gets his bat out in front to defend.
Short and angling in, on the off stump, David Bedingham goes deep in the crease and pats it back to the bowler.
Fuller and on off, driven past cover for a single by Wiaan.
Speared in, short and on middle, Mulder goes back and jabs it to mid-wicket.
Honing in on the off stump, Wiaan Mulder presses forward to block.
Very full, right at the toes, Mulder squeezes it out to short mid-wicket.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! The extra bit of bounce does the trick! Tanaka Chivanga bowls it on the back of a length, just around the fifth stump line. Matthew Breetzke gets a bit surprised with the extra bit of bounce as he looks to defend it from the crease and tries to take the bottom hand off the bat, but ends up getting an outside edge to third slip. Brian Bennett, standing there, takes a sharp catch to his right. Matthew Breetzke departs on 13 (45). South Africa are two down for 21.
Matthew Breetzke c B Bennett b T Chivanga 13 (45b 1x4 0x6)
Short of a length, on the middle and off. Breetzke ducks underneath it.
Back of a length, on off. Matthew Breetzke blocks it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, around off. Matthew Breetzke dabs it towards gully.
BEATEN! Bowled it on the back of a length, around off stump. Hint of away movement on that one, and Matthew Breetzke looks to poke at it from the crease and gets beaten on the outside edge.

Bowled it on a fuller length from over the wicket. Sliding down the leg side, Matthew Breetzke looks to flick that one misses it. The ball rolls off his pads past the left of the diving keeper to the deep fine leg region, and two leg byes are taken.
Darted in fuller, on the stumps. Wiaan Mulder drives it back to the bowler.
Shortish and outside off. Matthew Breetzke cuts that one from the back foot to deep point for a single.
Fuller and around off. Matthew Breetzke works it towards the off side.
Tossed up, on the middle and leg. Matthew Breetzke lunges forward and blocks it to the leg side.
Slower and fuller, outside off. Wiaan Mulder drives it to the cover region for one.
Fuller and sliding in with the arm. Wiaan Mulder blocks it back to the bowler.
On a good length, angling onto the pads. Wiaan Mulder tucks it away to short mid-wicket for a single.
Drops it on the back of a length, around the fifth stump line. Wiaan Mulder gets on the back foot and blocks it to off side.
Full length, on the stumps. Hint of away movement on that one. Wiaan Mulder blocks it back to the bowler.
On the back of a length, angling bit away from off. Matthew Breetzke plays it with soft hands and taps it to point for a quick single.
Touch fuller this time, outside off. Matthew Breetzke shoulders arms at it.
Starts from over the wicket, pitches it on the good length, angling into the batter. Matthew Breetzke works it to the mid on region with a straight bat.
Sliding on, full and on middle, Mulder wrists it to mid-wicket.
Darted in, full and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and on off, punched to deep cover for one.

Leading edge but safe! Floated up by Wellington Masakadza, on middle, Matthew Breetzke steps out and tries to whip it away on the leg side with a closed bat face. Gets a leading edge that goes uppishly but evades the man at cover to his right and lands well away from the man at mid off to his left. Breetzke collects a couple.
Slower and fuller, tighter as well, on the off stump, Matthew Breetzke tentatively defends.
Matthew Breetzke will feel that he missed out here! A half-tracker, width offered on off, Breetzke slaps it hard but can't get it past the man at backward point.
DIshes it out on a hard length, on off, Mulder gets on his toes and gets closer to the line to block it out.
This is on a short of a length, on off, Breetzke drops it with soft hands in front of cover-point and takes a quick single.

FOUR! Fine shot and that will help Matthew Breetzke feel a lot better! On a good length, on off, Breetzke presses on the front foot and plays it right under his eyes. Just a punch past cover and the outfield does the rest.
Serves it on a short of a length, Matthew Breetzke dabs it away from his body towards point.
Outside off, on a length, left alone by Breetzke.
Lovely! On a good length, just outside the off stump, Matthew Breetzke defends inside the line and gets beaten on the outside edge but did well not to follow the ball as it goes away.
Sprayed on the pads, on a length, Mulder flicks it to the left of deep fine leg for a couple of runs.
Angling in and then nibbling away, on a nagging length, Wiaan Mulder guides it towards backward point.

It could have been trouble had the throw been to the bowling end! On a back of a length, on middle, Mulder turns it away past short leg and it rolls in the vacant backward square leg region. Wiaan wants the second run but Breetzke is late to turn. The keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga, gets to the ball quickly, turns around and fires in a throw at the batting end where Mulder gets in comfortably.
Delivers it on a back of a length, over off, Wiaan gets on his toes and dabs it down on the off side.
On a short of a length, on off, Mulder punches it to cover from the crease.
Shaping away, on a hard length, around off, Wiaan Mulder steers it off the back foot towards gully.
Outside off, dug in short, Matthew Breetzke ducks and lets the ball go through.
On a good length, in the channel on off, a watchful leave from Breetzke. The ball keeps climbing and the keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga takes it over his head.
Matthew Breetzke is squared up as the ball lands and jags away, on a nagging length, on middle. Manages to block it out neatly.
Around off, on a nagging length, Breetzke plays a bit away from his body and pushes it to cover.
Nipping back in, on a back of a length, over off and middle. Matthew Breetzke gets his bat and gloves away from the line of the ball to leave the ball on length. The ball bounces over the stumps.
Blessing Muzarabani bangs it in short, over off, Matthew Breetzke ducks under it.
End of a successful over from Tanaka Chivanga! Outside off, on a length, Mulder lets it be.
On a good length, on middle, Wiaan Mulder gets right behind it.

OUT! EDGED AND TAKEN! No mistake this time and Tony de Zorzi has been put out of his misery. Tanaka hits the length hard and serves it on a back of a length, on off, Tony gets on his toes and is better off leaving the ball alone. Ends up jabbing at the ball with hard hands. The ball nibbles away to catch the outside edge and it goes low to third slip. Brian Bennett gets low enough and gets his fingers under the ball to snaffle it. Tony de Zorzi departs for 0 (16) and South Africa are 3/1.
Tony de Zorzi c B Bennett b T Chivanga 0 (16b 0x4 0x6)
Closer to the off stump, on a good length, left alone by Tony.
Outside off, on a good length, Tony de Zorzi shoulders arms.

Tanaka Chivanga is on the money straight away! Tailing back in sharply from around the wicket, on a nagging length, not that wide for the cut but Tony de Zorzi goes for it. There is a bit of a steep bounce as well and due to the movement, Tony ends up chopping it beside the stumps.
On a good length, on middle and leg, dabbed down on the leg side.

Beaten! Blessing Muzarabani continues to make the two openers dance to his tunes. On a hard length, seaming away, around off, Matthew Breetzke hops and is better off leaving it alone but ends up having a fiddle before trying to withdraw his bat. Gets beaten on the outside edge.

Sprayed down leg, on the fuller side, Matthew Breetzke misses out on the tickle. The keeper, Tafadzwa Tsiga, with a half shout for caught behind but turned down. Remember, there is no DRS for this series.
Dug in short by Blessing, over off, Matthew Breetzke ducks under it.

Slanting into the right-hander, on a back of a length, Breetzke hops to work it away with the angle on the leg side. The ball nips back in and kicks up a bit to go past the inside edge and catch him on the thigh pad.
Lands it on a nagging length from over the wicket, on middle, Matthew Breetzke gets on his toes to keep it out with a straight bat.
Full and around off, Matthew Breetzke drives it along the ground to deep cover for a single.
Continues to bowl it straight, full and on middle, Matthew defends it off the front foot.
Very full, angling in, at the toes, Breetzke jams it out to cover.
Full again, attacking the stumps, Breetzke lunges to block it out.
Floated up, fuller and on middle, Matthew Breetzke is solid with his front foot defence.
Spinning away, short and on off, Matthew Breetzke cuts it straight to point.
On middle, on a short of a length, this kicks up a bit and catches Tony de Zorzi on the glove as he gets behind it to defend. Luckily for Tony, the ball does not pop up and goes down on the ground.

Well bowled! Angled in and then it straightens off the deck, on a good length, on off, Tony de Zorzi is beaten on the outside edge due to the seam movement as he shapes to flick it away. The ball zips past the bat to catch him high on the thigh pad.
On off, on a nagging length, de Zorzi plays it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Blessing goes a bit full this time and gets the ball to jag back in, on off, Tony de Zorzi looks to get behind the line but ekes out an inside edge onto the pads.
This keeps rising, on a shortish length, on off, Tony de Zorzi gets on top of the bounce and stabs it down the deck.
Sliding down leg, on a back of a length from around the wicket, Tony de Zorzi fails to help it away.
Tossed up again, on off, Breetzke leans ahead and eases it to cover.
A hint of turn, on off, Matthew gets a good stride in to smother the spin.
Keeps it nice and full, on off, Matthew Breetzke gets forward to block.
Floated up, full and on off, driven to cover where there is a slight misfield but the batters do not run on the misfield.
Matthew Breetzke and South Africa are underway! Way too short by Wellington, on off, Breetzke rocks back and cuts it to the left of deep cover for a couple of runs to open his account.
This slides on with the arm, on a nagging length, on middle, Matthew Breetzke goes back and dabs it towards backward point.
Angled in at the hips, on a short of a good length, de Zorzi gets on his toes and nudges it beside the pitch on the leg side.
On a hard length, this climbs onto the batter, Tony de Zorzi hops and keeps it out.

CHANCE GOES DOWN! It would have been an ideal start for Zimbabwe! Blessing makes the batter play this time, angling in, in the channel on off, Tony hangs back and could have left it on length but ends up presenting a straight bat to block. The ball nips away off the deck to catch the outside edge and it goes low towards second slip. Sean Williams gets low to take it around his right ankle but fails to hold on. It pops up and it is taken at first slip but the replays show that the ball went into ground after being shelled by Sean and then it was snapped up at first slip.
Banged into the wicket, well outside off, an easy leave for Tony.
Blessing goes into the wicket again but down leg, Tony de Zorzi gets inside the line for the tickle but fails to lay any bat on it.

A brute of a delivery first up! Blessing Muzarabani steams in from around the wicket, bends his back and hits the deck hard, around middle and leg. Not all that short and Tony looks to initially duck under it before deciding to get inside the line and let the ball go past him. He fails to get out of the way in time and the ball catches him on the left shoulder.
